item_2.Description: This bottle is full of clean, delicious water. It can be drunk to recover a little energy, and has a million other uses.
item_2.Name: Bottle of Water

item_3.Description: Learn a simple word of power.
item_3.Name: Word of Power Scroll (level 1)

item_4.Description: Learn a simple word of power.
item_4.Name: Word of Power Scroll (level 2)

item_51.Description: WARNING! This spittle is contaminated with the Lycanthropy disease. Drinking it will make you a werewolf instantly and forever! There is NO cure.
item_51.Name: Werewolf Spit

item_52.Description: Test potion transforms you into a pig. Permanent until dispelled! WARNING: think before you drink!
item_52.Name: Pig Juice

item_54.Description: Test potion transforms you into a deer. Permanent until dispelled! WARNING: think before you drink!
item_54.Name: Deer Juice

item_56.Description: Use this wolf whistle on the strange dais in the woods.
item_56.Name: Wolf Whistle

item_57.Description: A mage's journal. Most of the pages are turning to dust, but one dog-eared page has been magically preserved by someone.
item_57.Name: Dusty Journal

item_59.Description: A primer on Combat Psychology. (Raises your skill to 1 if you don't know Combat Psychology.)
item_59.Name: Fighting with Psychology

item_60.Description: A chisel with a magical tip designed to chip away magical crystal.
item_60.Name: Geomancy Awl

item_61.Description: Dear player, thank you for completing this quest. If this were a complete MMO, you would have received a fun reward now. Maybe next time! - Eric
item_61.Name: I.O.U. Quest Reward

item_62.Description: Hold down Shift to run very, very fast. You also take no damage from falls.
item_62.Name: Super Speed Potion

item_63.Description: Teaches you the basics of Teleportation. (Raises your skill to 1 if it isn't already.)
item_63.Name: Teleportation For Beginners

item_64.Description: Teaches you the basics of Archery. (Raises your skill to 1 if it isn't already.)
item_64.Name: Archery For Imbeciles

item_65.Description: Teaches you the basics of Fletching. (Raises your skill to 1 if it isn't already.)
item_65.Name: I'd Rather Be Fletching

item_66.Description: Teaches you how to performed Unarmed kicks. Only useful if you somehow managed to get turned into an animal before learning the Unarmed Kick ability. (Raises your Unarmed skill to 1 if it isn't already.)
item_66.Name: Kicking Your Way To Murder

item_69.Description: Test potion transforms you into a spider. Permanent until dispelled! WARNING: think before you drink!
item_69.Name: Spider Juice

item_71.Description: Teaches you the Myconian language. (This is a testing aid and will not be available for long; please use this to test the Myconian dungeon, which can be accessed via random brown mushrooms in Serbule.)
item_71.Name: Myconian Primer

item_72.Description: Lets you fly (press the Move Up key to begin). You'll take no damage from falls while the effect lasts.
item_72.Name: Flight Potion

item_73.Description: You become a raven. Use the Move Up key to fly. Your attacks will do negligible damage. But you can fly, so that's something.
item_73.Name: Raven Potion

item_74.Description: Teaches you how to survey, find minerals, and mine ore. (Raises your skill in Surveying, Geology, and Mining to 1 if they aren't already.)
item_74.Name: Surveying Book

item_75.Description: Test potion transforms you into a cow. Permanent until dispelled! WARNING: think before you drink!
item_75.Name: Cow Juice

item_77.Description: It's a note labeled "To my dear friend."
item_77.Name: Note from Yurra

item_79.Description: Turns off PvP caused by PvP Juice test-potions.
item_79.Name: Un-PvP Juice

item_80.Description: Makes you PvP-flagged for a half hour. You can attack other players who are also PvP-flagged.
item_80.Name: PvP Juice (30 minutes)

item_81.Description: Makes you PvP for an hour.
item_81.Name: PvP Juice (60 minutes)

item_82.Description: Strange weeds that supposedly bring the dead back to life.
item_82.Name: Eternal Greens

item_83.Description: Makes you PvP against ALL players -- even ones who don't want to PvP! Used for live events only! Use UnPvPJuice to turn it off.
item_83.Name: Special PK Juice

item_84.Description: Potion transforms you into a GIGANTIC spider. Permanent until dispelled via UnspiderJuice. For live events only!
item_84.Name: Superspider Juice

item_85.Description: Teaches you how to create visual arts. (Raises your skill to 1 if it isn't already.)
item_85.Name: How To Be An Artist

item_86.Description: Test potion transforms you into a giant bat. Permanent until dispelled! WARNING: think before you drink!
item_86.Name: Bat Juice

item_88.Description: When you aren't in combat, hold down Shift to run very, very fast. You also take no damage from falls.
item_88.Name: Super Speed Potion

item_101.Description: Recovers 10 health per second for 30 seconds.
item_101.Name: Regeneration Potion

item_102.Description: Recovers 6 power per second for 30 seconds.
item_102.Name: Weak Power Regen Potion

item_103.Description: Recovers 15 power per second for 30 seconds.
item_103.Name: Strong Power Regen Potion

item_107.Description: Recovers 75 health and power, and recovers a bit more for 30 seconds
item_107.Name: Second-Wind Slushie

item_108.Description: Boost your maximum health by 100 for two minutes.
item_108.Name: Steroid Drink

item_109.Description: Recovers 100 power instantly, and recovers 120 more over 60 seconds
item_109.Name: Ultimate Energy Drink

item_110.Description: Recovers 20 power per second for 30 seconds.
item_110.Name: Potent Power Regen Potion

item_111.Description: Delicious gel boosts your maximum power by 100 for two minutes.
item_111.Name: Cranium Gel

item_115.Description: Boost your maximum health by 200 for two minutes.
item_115.Name: Super Steroid Drink

item_117.Description: Recovers 14 health per second for 30 seconds.
item_117.Name: Super Regeneration Potion

item_118.Description: Recovers 20 health per second for 30 seconds.
item_118.Name: Recuperative Honey Potion

item_119.Description: This admin-created utility potion repairs all items in your inventory that are broken due to deaths while in Hardcore mode.
item_119.Name: Item Repair Potion

item_121.Description: Dispels most curses, diseases, disfigurements, addictions, and botherments.
item_121.Name: Minor Panacea

item_122.Description: Dispels most curses, diseases, disfigurements, addictions, and botherments.
item_122.Name: Minor Panacea (Admin-Provided)

item_125.Description: It's unclear when this potion was made, but it's old. A tiny label declares it to be "the liquified essence of sharpness." It's mint flavored.
EffectDescs: For two minutes, all Slashing attacks deal +25 damage
item_125.Name: Sword Lord Potion

item_1001.Description: This handful of dirt is weird and smelly and damp.
item_1001.Name: Strange Dirt

item_1002.Description: A big chunk of red crystal. Kind of pretty. Not a normal crystal though. Seems manufactured.
item_1002.Name: Redwall Crystal

item_1003.Description: This bright red powder always feels warm to the touch.
item_1003.Name: Fire Dust

item_1005.Description: A small amount of smelly sulfur.
item_1005.Name: Sulfur

item_1006.Description: A tiny pinch of saltpeter, a strange substance with many magical uses.
item_1006.Name: Saltpeter

item_1009.Description: A small bundle of grass. Useful for taming and feeding most types of ungulates.
item_1009.Name: Grass

item_1010.Description: A weird old coin that seems strangely heavy.
item_1010.Name: Ancient Bronze Coin

item_1011.Description: Spun from the butt of a very big spider.
item_1011.Name: Spiderweb

item_1013.Description: Although still pretty, this shell took serious damage and is no longer structurally sound.
item_1013.Name: Giant Snail Shell

item_1014.Description: This shell is in amazing condition.
item_1014.Name: Perfect Giant Snail Shell

item_1015.Description: You would not believe how big this praying mantis was. Well, YOU might.
item_1015.Name: Giant Mantis Claw

item_1017.Description: This lump of flesh still pulses to an unknowable rhythm.
item_1017.Name: Nightmare Flesh

item_1018.Description: It looks stick-like, but it's incredibly strong.
item_1018.Name: Giant Spider Leg

item_1019.Description: Stick-like and covered in tiny hairs, this is not particularly pleasant to touch.
item_1019.Name: Spider Leg

item_1101.Description: This lovely goblet [vendor trash] is teeming with history [vendor trash] and you should probably treasure it forever [vendor trash].
item_1101.Name: Goblet

item_1102.Description: An old brown plate, the kind vendors really like for some reason. Maybe there's a collectibles market you're unaware of.
item_1102.Name: Plate

item_1103.Description: A scrawled note that says, "Please, we need food within a week or our entire village will surely starve. A king's ransom for anyone who comes to our aid!" Sadly, the date is from several years ago.
item_1103.Name: Plea For Food

item_1104.Description: A volume of elven verse. The rhymes are forced and the lines scan poorly, but hey, it's elven verse -- somebody will want this junk.
item_1104.Name: Elven Verse

item_1105.Description: Who knows what this ancient document says? The language has been lost to the ages. Judging by the accompanying stick-figure pornographic art, however, it's probably not really worth dwelling on.
item_1105.Name: Ancient Tutorial

item_1106.Description: It's empty, but the box itself is quite beautiful.
item_1106.Name: Filigreed Jewelry Box

item_1107.Description: A gross antique spoon. Not worth much... but perhaps you can find a spoon collector or something.
item_1107.Name: Spoon

item_1111.Description: These spider mandibles seem to be made of ivory! What will nature think of next?
item_1111.Name: Ivory Mandibles

item_1112.Description: This rhino horn is made of ivory. You could have sworn rhino horns were made of hardened fat, but nope, clearly you were wrong.
item_1112.Name: Ivory Horn

item_1113.Description: An ornately jeweled hairpin used by goblins of both sexes.
item_1113.Name: Jeweled Goblin Hairpin

item_1114.Description: A big canine from some animal. It's glowing, and is clearly enchanted. Fascinating.
item_1114.Name: Magic Tooth

item_1115.Description: A scrap of fur from a dead animal.
item_1115.Name: Tuft of Fur

item_1117.Description: Yep, the snout of a pig.
item_1117.Name: Pig Snout

item_1118.Description: A drop of some foul magical liquid.
item_1118.Name: Crossing Oil

item_1119.Description: A drop of sweet-smelling magical liquid.
item_1119.Name: Uncrossing Oil

item_1120.Description: A drop of magical liquid containing the essence of fear.
item_1120.Name: Fear Oil

item_1121.Description: A drop of magical liquid containing the essence of hatred.
item_1121.Name: Hatred Oil

item_1122.Description: A drop of magical liquid containing the essence of hope.
item_1122.Name: Hope Oil

item_1123.Description: A very large, well-made brass nail. Useful in Carpentry.
item_1123.Name: Brass Nail

item_1124.Description: A thin metal chain, now broken. It wasn't very high-quality in the first place, either.
item_1124.Name: Broken Necklace

item_1125.Description: It's a chunk of glass. Pretty much worthless, although a few Alchemy recipes require bits of glass.
item_1125.Name: Piece of Green Glass

item_1126.Description: This is an especially round pebble. But it's still just a pebble, with probably very few uses.
item_1126.Name: Perfectly Round Pebble

item_1127.Description: A thin scroll of goblin verse, focusing on the beauty of hard work, the wonders of nature, and the fairness of slavery. It has little value.
item_1127.Name: Goblin Poetry

item_1128.Description: It's a gross ivory spoon. Worth something to somebody... but not to you.
item_1128.Name: Ivory Spoon

item_1129.Description: An antique plate with careful metalwork. It's tarnished and dented, but still valuable.
item_1129.Name: Filigreed Plate

item_1130.Description:
"I don't know who you are, but you've got a lot of nerve using my storage box without permission. I sold all your stuff."

 - Ivyn
item_1130.Name: Letter From Ivyn

item_1131.Description: Velkort's masterpiece. Apparently the most difficult potion he's ever concocted. It tastes like beetle urine and it smells like burnt toast, and if you shake it too hard, you might blow up the countryside. But aside from those quirks... a masterpiece.
EffectDescs: For two minutes, all Fire Magic attacks deal +25 damage
item_1131.Name: Pure Heart of Flame

item_1132.Description: A tarnished ancient coin. It feels heavy and strangely cold.
item_1132.Name: Ancient Silver Coin

item_1133.Description: A tarnished ancient coin. It feels heavy and strangely cold.
item_1133.Name: Ancient Gold Coin

item_1134.Description: A small lobe from a Brain Bug. Wait, did... did it just pulse? Did you see that? No... probably your imagination.
item_1134.Name: Brain Bug Lobe

item_1135.Description: A brass gear the size of your hand. It has no obvious purpose.
item_1135.Name: Brass Gear

item_1136.Description: A small statue of a goblin. It was probably originally part of a child's toy army. Looks antique.
item_1136.Name: Brass Figurine

item_1137.Description: A lump of green poisonous ooze.
item_1137.Name: Toxic Sludge

item_1138.Description: The mandible of a giant insect or arthropod.
item_1138.Name: Oversized Mandible

item_1139.Description: A clump of feathers from a midsized bird.
item_1139.Name: Feathers

item_1140.Description: The beak of a midsized bird.
item_1140.Name: Beak

item_1141.Description: It's a pretty big rock. You could probably carve some thoroughly mediocre arrow heads out of it if you were patient enough.
item_1141.Name: Flinty Rock

item_1142.Description:
"Twenty godlings in the ground,
Twenty more in air surround,
One was killed in demon fire,
Two were banished to the mire."
item_1142.Name: Lawara's Notes

item_1143.Description: Nice goblin craftsmanship. Well, goblin oversight of slave craftsmanship, which is the same thing.
item_1143.Name: Shiny Plate

item_1144.Description: A spiky and bizarre tooth, as long as a dagger.
item_1144.Name: Worm Tooth

item_1145.Description: The claw of a bear that grew up around too much magic.
item_1145.Name: Enchanted Bear Claw

item_1148.Description: A small fleck of hardened dinosaur skin.
item_1148.Name: Small Dinosaur Scale

item_1150.Description: A snippet of a family tree. Probably valuable to somebody... but not to most.
item_1150.Name: Genealogy Chart

item_1151.Description: A poem written by a loved-one for a deceased family member, following an old Human custom. Since funerals are the only time these Humans ever wrote poetry in their lives, the quality is... not good.
item_1151.Name: Burial Poem

item_1153.Description: An enchanted block of ice that can never melt.
item_1153.Name: Ice Core

item_1154.Description: Stamped with the seal of an official Council representative, this certificate is redeemable for 1000 councils at the Statehelm Mint.
item_1154.Name: Council Certificate

item_1155.Description: A palm-sized chunk of hardened dinosaur hide.
item_1155.Name: Large Dinosaur Scale

item_1156.Description: A small bundle of grass from a dimension of darkness and despair. Useful for taming nightmare animals.
item_1156.Name: Evil Grass

item_1157.Description: A small runestone used by summoners to ensure the creatures they bring forth can't return to their native dimension. Clever animal handlers have found alternate uses for its potent magic.
item_1157.Name: Anchor Rune

item_1158.Description: These are just simple line drawings, but they were done by someone with masterful skill.
item_1158.Name: Ancient Sketchbook

item_1159.Description: It's a small bar of pleasant-smelling soap. And so smooth! This is nice soap.
item_1159.Name: Floral Soap

item_1161.Description: A small spindle of cotton string.
item_1161.Name: String

item_1162.Description: Made of painstakingly carved bone. It has very fine teeth for collecting insects out of hair.
item_1162.Name: Louse Comb

item_1163.Description: These shackles would only fit small creatures, such as fey or possibly dwarves.
item_1163.Name: Cold Iron Shackles

item_1164.Description: A small painted wooden chip, used in card and parlor games.
item_1164.Name: Red Game Chip

item_1165.Description: A small painted wooden chip, used in card and parlor games. It has tiny flecks of inlaid gemstone, making it slightly harder for rogues to slip counterfeits into a game.
item_1165.Name: Green Game Chip

item_1166.Description: A small painted wooden chip, used in card and parlor games. The paint is magical, and protects it from being replicated by illusion spells –- a common ploy amongst dwarven rogues and hustlers.
item_1166.Name: Yellow Game Chip

item_1167.Description: Magical runes have been etched into this claw to cause acidic explosions. Unfortunately the etchings weakened the chitin, and it's not suitable for use in constructing armor.
item_1167.Name: Augmented Mantis Claw

item_1168.Description: A big chunk of glass infused with intellect-improving magic. It could make animals smarter permanently. Or you could use it on yourself, but the effects would only last a while.
EffectDescs: Raises Max Power by 15 for 30 minutes
item_1168.Name: Mind Enhancement Gem

item_1169.Description: A large hook-shaped bone. Pretty sharp.
item_1169.Name: Bone Hook

item_1171.Description: The core of a myconian. It is inedible and has no obvious use, but it somehow feels useful. To somebody.
item_1171.Name: Heartshroom

item_1172.Description: A thick greenish goo. It tastes delicious! Useful in both alchemical potions and specialty baked goods. [Recipes not yet implemented, but coming soon.]
item_1172.Name: Myconian Jelly

item_1173.Description: A fairly fragile bone that was part of some animal's rib cage.
item_1173.Name: Rib Bone

item_1174.Description: A comb in the orcish style, made of bone and dipped in gold. Worn as jewelry.
item_1174.Name: Orcish Hair Comb

item_1175.Description: Very old seeds that can't be planted anymore, but may have other uses due to their glowing magical nature. Perhaps druids or shamans would like them. Or seed collectors.
item_1175.Name: Enchanted Holly Seeds

item_1176.Description: A petrified glass tube made when lightning strikes sand. Alchemists love these, and fletchers use them for some advanced arrows.
item_1176.Name: Fulgurite

item_1177.Description: A sort of "cheat sheet" for ancient scribes. Perhaps it'd be useful in recreating lost Calligraphy secrets.
item_1177.Name: Ancient Stencil

item_1178.Description: A bit of sea sponge that's been soaked in something weird. Smells like camphor and... something else you can't place. Supposedly these sponges absorb ambient magic and can be used in potions.
item_1178.Name: Ambient Magic Sponge

item_1179.Description: A small orcish utility knife, a little too short to be useful as a weapon. A few years ago, these were a fashionable accessory in Statehelm, but the fad has died out now.  ( Not to be confused with the orcish Khopesh, which is a very dangerous sword.)
item_1179.Name: Khopis

item_1181.Description: A bit of mistletoe with a soft green glow. Probably pretty useful for druids. Exotic plant collectors would like it, too.
item_1181.Name: Enchanted Mistletoe

item_1182.Description: A hand-carved spoon made of bone. One the one hand, gross! On the other hand, it's a quality hand-made item, with a certain primitive charm. No, wait. No. It's just gross.
item_1182.Name: Bone Spoon

item_1183.Description:
This odd organic life stores solar energy in an unusual manner: it shunts it into a tiny pocket dimension. This allows the lichen to thrive in any sunlit environment, but it's most commonly found in freezing areas because there are fewer natural predators.

It is used by sages as a sort of battery for spells that require a large burst of power, and surveyors claim that the lichen can be used to find hidden caches of minerals in the area.
item_1183.Name: Tundra Lichen

item_1184.Description: A small leather sack of weird powders and bones, useful for casting Orcish magics. It is worn prominently by Orcish wizards as a symbol of their power.
item_1184.Name: Orcish Spell Pouch

item_1185.Description: A conveniently-sized shovel, perfect for digging small graves. (With this in your inventory, you will have the option of burying the corpses of deceased monsters. Burying monsters will make replacement monsters appear more quickly.)
item_1185.Name: Shovel

item_1186.Description: A magical scroll that lets you play a word game.
item_1186.Name: Word Game

item_1187.Description: Ghost sweat, congealed into a slimy lump. Probably useful for crafting potions or something.
item_1187.Name: Ectoplasm

item_1188.Description: A rubbery eyestalk from a watcher.
item_1188.Name: Eyestalk

item_1189.Description: The desiccated remains of a small animal that was caught and partially digested by a carnivorous plant or giant spider or something horrible like that.
item_1189.Name: Powdered Mammal

item_1190.Description: The long tongue of a frog-like creature.
item_1190.Name: Rubbery Tongue

item_1191.Description: The broken-off wing of a dead fairy. Broken fairy wings are a horrific, nauseating sight to other fairies.
item_1191.Name: Fairy Wing

item_1192.Description: A lump of flesh from a troll. It automatically regenerates at the same rate that it rots.
item_1192.Name: Troll Flesh

item_1193.Description: The stinky guts of a gigantic snail.
item_1193.Name: Snail Sinews

item_1194.Description: A broken-off piece of a zombie. It stinks quite badly, but doesn't seem to be rotting too quickly...
item_1194.Name: Zombified Hand

item_1195.Description: Someone killed an ogre and took its stomach. That's not disturbing at all. Perfectly reasonable thing to do.
item_1195.Name: Ogre Stomach

item_1196.Description: A small cloth satchel containing special powder that can be used to commune with the dead.
item_1196.Name: Fetish Bag

item_1197.Description: A small painted statue of an ogre. It was probably originally part of a child's toy army. Looks antique, but not very valuable.
item_1197.Name: Lead Figurine of an Ogre

item_1198.Description: A small painted statue of a goblin. It was probably originally part of a child's toy army. Looks antique, but not very valuable.
item_1198.Name: Lead Figurine of a Goblin

item_1199.Description: A small painted statue of a skeleton. It was probably originally part of a child's toy army. Looks antique, but not very valuable.
item_1199.Name: Lead Figurine of a Skeleton

item_1200.Description: A small painted statue of a hag. It was probably originally part of a child's toy army. Looks antique, but not very valuable.
item_1200.Name: Lead Figurine of a Hag

item_1201.Description: A small brass figurine of a hag. It was probably originally part of a child's toy army. Looks antique, and somewhat valuable.
item_1201.Name: Brass Figurine of a Hag

item_1202.Description: A scale from a dragon! Hmm, it'd be a pretty small dragon... or, more likely, some dragon-kin creature.
item_1202.Name: Small Yellow Dragon Scale

item_1203.Description: A scale from a dragon! Hmm, it'd be a pretty small dragon... or, more likely, some dragon-kin creature.
item_1203.Name: Small Red Dragon Scale

item_1204.Description: A scale from a dragon! Hmm, it'd be a pretty small dragon... or, more likely, some dragon-kin creature.
item_1204.Name: Small Green Dragon Scale

item_1205.Description: A scale from a dragon! Hmm, it'd be a pretty small dragon... or, more likely, some dragon-kin creature.
item_1205.Name: Small Blue Dragon Scale

item_1206.Description: It looks like a coin, and it's made of some strong metal, but it has no markings or denomination. Whatever it's for, it's very old.
item_1206.Name: Lost Currency

item_1207.Description: This chunk of spider came off in one solid piece. It's probably useful for making armor, if you like wearing creepy ridiculous things as armor.
item_1207.Name: Spider Carapace

item_1208.Description: The end of a basilisk's tail, said to be a potent natural magic source.
item_1208.Name: Basilisk Tail Tip

item_1209.Description: The end of a manticore's tail, with the venom sack intact.
item_1209.Name: Manticore Tail Tip

item_1210.Description: A saliva-covered ball of hair. The hair is unusual and perhaps valuable, but not when there's spit all over it.
item_1210.Name: Giant Hairball

item_1211.Description: A small stone. It's said to be the final remains of a ghost who somehow found peace.
item_1211.Name: Spirit Stone

item_1212.Description: A brain that's been preserved in some sort of alchemical soup.
item_1212.Name: Pickled Brain

item_1214.Description: A jaggedly-carved stone block, warm to the touch. Dwarven safety runes indicate that it is explosive, poisonous, and ... there's one other danger symbol that you don't recognize.
item_1214.Name: Dwarven N Core

item_1215.Description: Upon activation, this small stone explodes, typically killing the person activating it. These runes are used by paranoid merchants as anti-theft devices. Intermediate runecrafters and fire mages can also make use of them in their research.
item_1215.Name: Explosive Runestone

item_1216.Description: It's stone, egg-shaped, and it came off of a gargoyle. Whether it's an actual embryonic gargoyle is not readily apparent.
item_1216.Name: Gargoyle Egg

item_1217.Description: A mostly-used-up candle made of lard.
item_1217.Name: Candle Stump

item_1218.Description: A small crystalline prism. Transmuters use these to guide phlogiston into or out of an item.
item_1218.Name: Prism

item_1220.Description: Salvaged from some ancient public works project, this magic nail gives extra resilience to complex carpentry items.
item_1220.Name: Enchanted Construction Nail

item_1221.Description:
This small bag of sand is somehow different from regular sand. You can't tell exactly how or why it's different, but you know it is.

Magic sand is coveted by crazy prospectors, who claim there's a way to use the sand to reveal vast mineral wealth.
item_1221.Name: Magic Sand

item_1222.Description: What a find! This is an intact biped arm assembly: humerus, radius, ulna, even most of the phalanges!
item_1222.Name: Arm Bones

item_1223.Description: This book threatens to crumble to dust if you so much as open the cover. It would take a master librarian to get any knowledge from this old specimen.
item_1223.Name: Tattered Red Book

item_1224.Description: The weird symbols on the cover seem intriguing, but the pages are so faded and ruined that you can't make out any words. Perhaps an expert librarian could make some use of it.
item_1224.Name: Faded Blue Book

item_1225.Description: A small statuette of a wizard in battle armor, his arm outstretched as he casts a spell. It was probably originally part of a child's toy set. Looks antique, but only moderately valuable.
item_1225.Name: Lead Figurine of a War Wizard

item_1226.Description: Two ordinary Council Screeds glued together by a prankster.
item_1226.Name: Glued Coins

item_1227.Description: A small clay-fired pot. It has long cracks that make it less than ideal for holding water, but maybe somebody could patch it up or something. Just... not you.
item_1227.Name: Leaky Clay Pot

item_1228.Description: A piece of an old clay pot. It might fetch a few coins from a vendor if you make up a history for this piece of junk.
item_1228.Name: Pottery Shard

item_1229.Description: Lac is secreted from some types of insects, most notably the lac insect. It is used in creating shellac, which is a versatile crafting resource.
item_1229.Name: Lac

item_1230.Description: Secreted from gigantic insects, this substance is used in making very high-quality shellac.
item_1230.Name: Ultra Lac

item_1236.Description: It's labeled "Evil Tasks For Today", but all the tasks involve shopping and housekeeping.
item_1236.Name: Evil To-Do List

item_1237.Description: It's a blank form for requesting personal military items from the Ankara.
item_1237.Name: Ankara Requisition Form

item_1238.Description: It's about nature. It's boring and it doesn't even rhyme.

item_6107.Description: An unusual tea with a strong kick.

item_6108.Description: This drink has a not-too-great flavor, but it's very good at rehydrating tired bodies. The preferred desert beverage of people who are too rich to drink water.
item_6108.Name: Hydration Punch

item_6109.Description: Venison fried in butter and coated in fresh-cracked pepper. An amazing snack!
item_6109.Name: Pepper Venison

item_6110.Description: A delicious snack food. It's ... some sort of meat... drenched in a sweet sauce and wrapped in dough. Selaxi refuses to part with the recipe.
item_6110.Name: Selaxi's Scorpion Stinger

item_6111.Description: A tasty beverage of cactus juice and some sweet ingredient Selaxi refuses to share.
item_6111.Name: Selaxi's Cactus Mixer

item_6112.Description: An invention of the yeti people, this kabob-like snack is best eaten before you learn the ingredients.
item_6112.Name: Yeti Stick

item_6113.Description: A yeti invention of boiled mutton in matted fir. The stench is impressive. The taste is unique, and not as bad as you'd expect.
item_6113.Name: Furpot

item_6115.Description: A pie so good that it would be foolish to eat it as just a dessert. Eat it as a meal.
item_6115.Name: Fancy Pumpkin Pie

item_6116.Description: Hard on the outside, runny liquid on the inside. Mmm...
item_6116.Name: Soft-Boiled Egg

item_6117.Description: Runny and hot and covered in salt and pepper. Ideal with some bread.
item_6117.Name: Poached Egg

item_6118.Description: This is just some raw eggs in a glass, blended with a little milk. Gross.
item_6118.Name: Raw Egg Blend

item_6119.Description: Somebody wove some long bacon strips into a sort of bowl. And then put chunks of fried meat into the bowl. Weird. Salty.
item_6119.Name: Bacon Basket

item_6120.Description: It's a scrambled egg, beloved breakfast of nearly every sentient race.
item_6120.Name: Scrambled Egg

item_6121.Description: It's... a clownfish. Dried and salted. Snack-sized.
item_6121.Name: Dried Clownfish

item_6123.Description: A well-preserved and salted fish, perfect for snacking.
item_6123.Name: Dried Grapefish

item_6124.Description: A well-preserved and salted fish. This makes an amazing snack!
item_6124.Name: Dried Perch

item_6127.Description: A well-preserved and salted fish. An ... interesting... snack.
item_6127.Name: Dried Cave Fish

item_6128.Description: Low-quality pieces of cat meat have been sliced extraordinarily thin, tenderized, and then buried in salt. The result is a cup of hot stew that tastes ... salty. But not horrible.
item_6128.Name: Cat Stew Cup

item_6129.Description: Cat meat coated in a thick orange sauce. Surprisingly not terrible.
item_6129.Name: Orange Cat

item_6130.Description: The perfect seasonings make cat meat not just palatable, but actually tasty.
item_6130.Name: Spicy Lemon Cat

item_6131.Description: Dried meat and fish in a secret blend of spices.
item_6131.Name: Nishika's Travel Snack

item_6401.Description: Baked beets in a succulent, simple glaze.
item_6401.Name: Glazed Beets

item_6402.Description: A loaf of warm, moist banana bread.
item_6402.Name: Banana Bread

item_6405.Description: A delicious treat: a banana shallow-fried in sugary butter.
item_6405.Name: Fried Banana

item_6406.Description: A blend of baked vegetables in a hearty cheese sauce.
item_6406.Name: Cheesy Veggie Delight

item_6407.Description: Tasty crabmeat in a makeshift bun. Lemony!
item_6407.Name: Crab Roll

item_6451.Description: This is an incredibly unappealing piece of rotten meat.
EffectDescs: Food Poisoning: Heavy poison damage over time masks beneficial effect
item_6451.Name: Maggoty Ham

item_11109.Name: Iocaine Powder

item_11110.Description: A carefully tweaked dose of iocaine powder, designed to make you very ill but not kill you, allowing the body to build up resistance to the deadly toxin.
item_11110.Name: Iocaine Practice Dose

item_11201.Name: Basic Spore Bomb

item_11202.Description: A spore bomb, designed to be tossed as a weapon by a seasoned Mycologist.

item_11221.Name: Lycanspore Bomb

item_12001.Description: This unidentified pastoral seems to be in good condition.
item_12001.Name: Unidentified Painting

item_12002.Description: This idyllic scene seems to have stood the passage of time quite well.
item_12002.Name: Unidentified Painting

item_12003.Description: This painting depicts a long-lost monument. Rather pretty.
item_12003.Name: Unidentified Painting

item_12004.Description: This nature scene was painted with vibrant colors.
item_12004.Name: Unidentified Painting

item_12005.Description: There is a hint of melancholy behind this beautiful nature scene.
item_12005.Name: Unidentified Painting

item_12006.Description: This pleasant abstract painting has a nice solid frame.
item_12006.Name: Unidentified Painting

item_12007.Description: A nature scene with an incredible level of detail.
item_12007.Name: Unidentified Painting

item_12031.Description: A musty tome. Looks tedious, if you judge it by its cover.
item_12031.Name: Unidentified Poetry Book

item_12032.Description: A thin volume of poetry. No pictures at all.
item_12032.Name: Unidentified Poetry Book

item_12101.Description: This is a novice students' attempt to mimic Landrisil's masterpiece, "The Forest Before Dusk".
item_12101.Name: Student Painting

item_12102.Description: The tell-tale signs of Newakis fatbrush-strokes indicate that this is a novice goblin painting, probably a teenagers' efforts.
item_12102.Name: Mediocre Goblin Painting

item_12103.Description: This is the work of an elven artisan from approximately 300 years ago. It has a slight kitsch factor, and may look good on a wall, but it has little monetary value.
item_12103.Name: Forest Painting

item_12104.Description: This nature scene depicts Traticus, the mythical elven hero, entering the Woods of Disdain. The subject matter dates the painting to the New Revisionist period, 150 years ago. By elven timelines this was very recent, making the painting extremely tacky. Perhaps it will gain value in 300 years, however.
item_12104.Name: Painting of Traticus

item_12105.Description: This is clearly the work of a skilled goblin artisan. Made in the recent Three Hierarchies goblin style, it is probably very new.
item_12105.Name: Goblin Painting

item_12106.Description: A lovely forgery of "Snake Widow Lake" by Hermard Torsitan, the most esteemed living human painter.
item_12106.Name: "Snake Widow Lake"

item_12107.Description: This painting of a waterfall is bland and uninspired, but you can barely make out an older, better painting underneath. The older painting looks to have been a practice piece by a goblin expert.
item_12107.Name: Bland Waterfall Painting

item_12108.Description: A mass-produced replica of Sherig's "Ovallia". Tacky and somewhat low-quality, but it's currently popular among the nouveau riche.
item_12108.Name: "Ovallia"

item_12109.Description: This is an original numbered Ertrigard painting. The master is beloved for waterfall scenes like this one. However, thanks to his magic brush, he created over 40,000 paintings during his lifetime, so being "original" doesn't really make it too terribly special.
item_12109.Name: Numbered Ertrigard Painting

item_12110.Description: The painting is a student effort by an untrained hand, but the frame is quite lovely.
item_12110.Name: Well-Framed Painting

item_12111.Description: This depiction of the Tower of Treason was made by an elven Phot craftsman, using their signature one-bristle brush.
item_12111.Name: Phot Painting

item_12112.Description: A breathtaking scene of the old Council grounds of Ema. It seems to be 3000 years old. Sadly, however, there are traces of alteration magic in the paint, and it could well be a forgery.
item_12112.Name: Painting of Ema

item_12113.Description: This ugly piece has been preserved through the ages solely because it depicts Grigtekark, a goblin holy land.
item_12113.Name: Painting of Grigtekark

item_12114.Description: A stunning find! This is a truly ugly painting, but the lack of depth and proportion suggest that it was made by someone in the pre-Council era, making it at least 10,000 years old.
item_12114.Name: Extremely Old Painting

item_12115.Description: A lovely scene. Perhaps it was created by Mirkym -- it has her signature approach to foliage -- but probably just created in the same style by an admirer of her work.
item_12115.Name: Peaceful Scene

item_12116.Description: This piece is absolutely stunning... literally. Its magical pigments cause the viewer to very briefly lose their balance when viewing the painting. It's also a lovely painting and you're not sure why the artist bothered with the trickery.
item_12116.Name: Stunning Painting

item_12117.Description: A blurry watercolor without much to redeem it. However, it was made with highly magical elven pigments that can be reclaimed.
item_12117.Name: Blurry Pastoral

item_12118.Description: A gorgeous replica of Crea's "Esoteria", complete with all 88 hidden symbols. Most noticeable is the three-headed duck in one corner, representing the three states of nature.
item_12118.Name: "Esoteria"

item_12119.Description: An original work by an elven name you don't recognize, Errasteria. It's lovely.
item_12119.Name: "Clouds and Trees"

item_12120.Description: As you glance into this painting, the details seem to melt away. It is a cursed forgery of Gobblenuk's Forger's Peril: the insane goblin artist concocted a magical painting that can never be replicated. Any attempt to do so results in this monstrous visual effect. On the other hand, the visual effect is pretty sweet.
item_12120.Name: "Forgers Peril"

item_12121.Description: It's the little-known masterpiece by dwarven artist Kot Bhenul. Note the beautiful use of real gold in the paint.
item_12121.Name: "Last Autumn Sunset"

item_12122.Description: It's an extremely poor forgery of "Last Autumn Sunset" by Kot Bhenul. There isn't even any real gold in the gold paint!
item_12122.Name: Shoddy Forgery

item_12123.Description: A masterpiece in the vein of "Esoteria" or "The Cured Path", this symbol-laden mess of a painting contains over 400 secret meanings.
item_12123.Name: "Always The Way"

item_12124.Description: A recreation of the famous painting from the end of the Dwarven Period. The detail work really captures the ham-fisted spirit of dwarven painting techniques.
item_12124.Name: "Grim's Death"

item_12125.Description: This quality replica of "Candlelight and Dawnlight" is overshadowed by its frame, a beautiful masterpiece without peer.
item_12125.Name: Ornately-Framed Painting

item_12126.Description: This scribbled mess is supposedly about pies, but it doesn't contain any recognizable shapes -- just ugly blobs. It's unsigned and unappealing.
item_12126.Name: "Pies Cooling On A Windowsill"

item_12127.Description: A collection of rectangles on a blue background painted by Susarex, an elf that was turned into a snake in a tragic zoo accident. The perfectly straight rectangles took Susarex over 200 hours to complete.
item_12127.Name: "The Day I Dared To Dream"

item_12128.Description: Not inspired, but quite pleasant to look at, this abstract piece would look good hanging in a Council official's office. It lends a little class to any room it's in.
item_12128.Name: Reasonably Nice Abstract Art

item_12129.Description: A signed and numbered copy of the famous painting by Go Hakomi, a dwarven master. He recently passed away, increasing this painting's value significantly.
item_12129.Name: Reproduction of "Fortress Five"

item_12130.Description: You can kind of make out little orc faces and little stork bodies in this abstract painting, although you have to squint. It's bright and upbeat, but you've never heard of the painter.
item_12130.Name: "Orcs and Storks"

item_12131.Description: A wintry woodland scene featuring a little elf girl crying. You don't recognize the artist's name, but it dates back at least 1300 years, so that's something.
item_12131.Name: "With The Wind On My Face I Can Never Smile"

item_12132.Description: A lovely beach scene depicting a gaggle of goblins crowded around a massive talking fish wearing a little hat. You recognize the subject matter: it's the goblin tale of The Bossy Fishlord. Painted by Agzak, a reasonably well-known goblin artist.
item_12132.Name: "Yap And The Big Catch"

item_12133.Description: A depiction of Talerra, the spectral God of Depression and Knowing the Truth. Her ghostly arm beckons as if she has some bad news to deliver. This painting seems supernaturally resilient, and it has probably been blessed by one of Talerra's few monk-priests. However, it's way too creepy to display in a home.
item_12133.Name: "Talerra At The New Moon"

item_12134.Description: A well-known painting by the dwarven artist Kot Bhenul. Signed and numbered! This is a great find.
item_12134.Name: "Wheat"

item_12135.Description: An artist's depiction of what a fifth season might be like, if there was one between winter and spring. It's lovely, but it pretty much just looks like winter to you.
item_12135.Name: "Seasons Beyond Winter"

item_12301.Description: A musty tome of poetry from the dwarven master Gammo. It has both the original Dwarven rhyming couplets and a Human translation. Perfect for the poetry lover in your life.
item_12301.Name: Gammo's "Legions of Stone"

item_12302.Description: The elven shock-poet Zini's famous work about how humankind might go extinct due to their prudishness, but will be saved by kind and promiscuous elves. It has a lot of depraved imagery, but also plenty of clever rhymes. A good gift for poetry lovers and those who appreciate a good porno. But not a good gift for especially uptight (or racist) Humans.
item_12302.Name: "The Fall of Man" by Zini

item_12303.Description: Written by an anonymous goblin poet, this melodramatic prose-poem is about worms that are used as food. It is not highly-acclaimed, but beginners to the art of poetry appreciation find it humorous.
item_12303.Name: "Worm Food"

item_12304.Description: A rollicking good tale about a bumbling oaf who finds a magic belt that makes him supernaturally strong. A book-length poem that is popular amongst commoners, but considered a bit too "low-brow" for the more discerning afficianado.
item_12304.Name: "The Magic Belt"

item_12305.Description: This is not a book of poetry, but a book on how to better appreciate poetry.
item_12305.Name: Poetry Primer

item_12306.Description: The well-known human philosopher Jim Hatcher tried his hand at poetry with this tacky volume. There are some hints of cleverness toward the end, for people who keep reading that long.
item_12306.Name: "Why Are There Bees" by Jim Hatcher

item_12307.Description: Written by an anonymous orc, this terse poem tells the story of the battle of Fok, where over a million orcs died. The author manages to deliver a glimpse into the horrors of war. It's said that the author was drawn and quartered for producing this work, and their works burned, but obviously some copies survived.
item_12307.Name: "Battle of Fok"

item_12308.Description:
The famous children's poem about Mort, the undead skeleton, who ultimately kills everyone he ever loved in life.

It's famous because the Council once declared it mandatory reading for all children at age 4. However, the sheer amount of crying and misery it caused eventually got them to relent.
item_12308.Name: "Who Loves Mort?"

item_12309.Description: The goblin poet Kaghat wrote this twee poem about the supposed "lost tribe" of goblins, noble creatures that were more in tune with nature. It's her least-popular work, but it's also so much shorter than her other works that many more copies exist.
item_12309.Name: "Rain Dances of the Lost Tribe"

item_12310.Description: A late chapbook by the elven master Enst. This is quite a find! After his banishment, Enst is said to have only spoken his poems aloud, so that only the treants of the Harshland Forest know his later works. This tome has been written in a very sloppy hand... perhaps a treant wrote it?
item_12310.Name: "Sunsets" by Enst

item_12311.Description: An anonymous poem about farming. It's very, very long -- so long that it has become a cult classic in its own way, as bored elves challenge each other to memorize the entire thing. Then one partner will recite it during sex; the first person to finish loses the challenge.
item_12311.Name: "Till The Land By Moonlight"

item_12312.Description: A deep, difficult chapbook by the late human poet Avery Lancaster. Her imagery is hauntingly beautiful, yet profoundly stupid at the same time. That's the mark of a true master.
item_12312.Name: "Horse, Carry My Topaz"

item_12313.Description: A hard-hitting book by the goblin poet Kaghat. It approaches the topic of slavery from every angle, and it pulls no punches. It's a very polarizing book in goblin culture. Kaghat herself claims that she was banished from her tribe because of this book, although her tribe vehemently denies this, saying that Kaghat just wandered into the desert one day and never came back.
item_12313.Name: "Commentary on Slavery"

item_12314.Description: A heavy volume of poems by the dwarven master Gammo. It even includes the poem "My Penis Is The Sunstone", which has been censored by the Dwarven Culture Group for over 500 years! This is a great find for poetry lovers, though dwarves may find it too embarrassing to own. Less prudish individuals tend to find Gammo's works uplifting and ennervating.
item_12314.Name: "Collected Works of Gammo"

item_12315.Description: This is a real treasure -- an original hand-copied manuscript by Zuk-Ghu, the orcish poet of Kur! Mocked by his people, Zuk-Ghu was forced to write and distribute his poems in secrecy. They are truly beautiful, though... if you're fluent in Orc. If you only know pidgin-Orc like most people, these poems are largely inscrutable.
item_12315.Name: "Kur Hauntings" by Zuk-Ghu

item_12401.Description: This unidentified portrait is remarkably lifelike.
item_12401.Name: Unidentified Painting

item_12402.Description: A portrait of Khyrulek's young daughter. She's a pale Human child, no more than five years old, and she looks miserable.
item_12402.Name: Portrait of Ursula

item_12403.Description: A thin volume of poetry by the goblin poet Gruzark. It has a homely, earthly feel. Which is poet-speak for "it sucks." It has some exciting bits, though. Better than nothing.
item_12403.Name: Gruzark's Chapbook

EffectDescs: Can be deployed as artwork that players can appreciate. Disappears after 10 minutes.

item_12506.Description: High-quality cotton fibers that have been cleaned and prepared.
item_12506.Name: Perfect Cotton

item_12551.Description: Cotton cloth that's extremely porous. Ideal for butter and certain cheeses.

item_12552.Description: Cotton cloth that's very porous. Ideal for use in creating mold cheeses.
item_12552.Name: Voile Muslin

item_12553.Description: Porous cotton that's resistant to heat. Ideal for creating hard cheeses.
item_12553.Name: Cheesecloth

item_12554.Description: Porous cotton that's resistant to heat. Ideal for creating mold cheeses that take a long time to ripen.
item_12554.Name: Fine Cheesecloth

item_12555.Description: Porous cotton that's resistant to heat. Ideal for storing fresh bread.
item_12555.Name: Breadcloth

item_12558.Description: A porous sticky cloth that's useful for some basic garments.
item_12558.Name: Basic Spider Silk

item_12559.Description: A sticky cloth that's ideal for certain types of clothing.
item_12559.Name: Spider Silk

item_12560.Description: This strange cloth is smooth and cool to the touch.
item_12560.Name: Strong Spider Silk

item_12561.Description: This strange cloth is luxurious to the touch, yet incredibly strong.
item_12561.Name: Extreme Spider Silk

item_12562.Description: This strange cloth is luxurious to the touch, yet incredibly strong.
item_12562.Name: Incredible Spider Silk

item_12563.Description: A bit of gauze that helps keep flowers organized in a flower arrangement.
item_12563.Name: Flower Wrap

item_12564.Description: A bit of very specialized cloth that is used by expert flower arrangers.
item_12564.Name: Flower Banding

item_13001.Name: Handsaw

item_13003.Description: A handful of long wood nails.
item_13003.Name: Strong Nails

item_13101.Description: Useful generic wood! Good for cooking, building, whittling, and who knows what else. Wow! What a find!
item_13101.Name: Oak Wood

item_13102.Description: Useful generic wood! Good for cooking, building, whittling, and who knows what else. Wow! What a find!
item_13102.Name: Maple Wood

item_13103.Description: Useful generic wood! Good for cooking, building, whittling, and who knows what else. Wow! What a find!
item_13103.Name: Cedar Wood

item_13151.Description: This piece of oak is an exemplar of its type! There are a few uses for this type of lumber, but often there is no need for such high quality. In that case, you can turn this into several pieces of typical-quality oak wood.
item_13151.Name: Perfect Oak Wood

item_13152.Description: This piece of maple is an exemplar of its type! There are a few uses for this type of lumber, but often there is no need for such high quality. In that case, you can turn this into several pieces of typical-quality maple wood.

item_13153.Description: This piece of cedar is an exemplar of its type! There are a few uses for this type of lumber, but often there is no need for such high quality. In that case, you can turn this into several pieces of typical-quality cedar wood.
item_13153.Name: Perfect Cedar Wood

item_13201.Description: Oak chips for smoking fish and meat.
item_13201.Name: Oak Wood Chips

item_13202.Description: Maple chips for smoking fish and meat.
item_13202.Name: Maple Wood Chips

item_13203.Description: Cedar chips for smoking fish and meat.
item_13203.Name: Cedar Wood Chips

item_13301.Name: Super-Shoddy Meditation Stool

item_13302.Description: A disposable stool for meditating. Use it near a Meditation Pillar to boost the duration of your meditation effects x3.

item_13362.Description: A somewhat-comfortable chair. Relaxing in it boosts your Armor Regeneration +2 for a time.

item_13401.Description: A collection of 1000 dowels that are the right length for becoming arrows, if a fletcher prepared them.
item_13401.Name: Oak Dowels

item_13402.Description: A collection of 1000 dowels that are the right length for becoming arrows, if a fletcher prepared them.
item_13402.Name: Maple Dowels

item_13403.Description: A collection of 1000 dowels that are the right length for becoming arrows, if a fletcher prepared them.

item_13404.Description: Holds 1000 dowels. Suitable for use by fletchers. The box can only be used once.
item_13404.Name: Empty Fletching Box

item_13452.Description: A small box for storing up to 4 items. Lasts for 5 minutes once deployed. (Each player that access the storage crate can store their own items. All storage crates allow access to the same items for that player.)
item_13452.Name: Shoddy Storage Crate

item_13455.Description: A box for storing up to 8 items. Lasts for 5 minutes once deployed. (Each player that access the storage crate can store their own items. All storage crates allow access to the same items for that player.)
item_13455.Name: Decent Storage Crate

item_13458.Description: A box for storing up to 12 items. Lasts for 5 minutes once deployed. (Each player that access the storage crate can store their own items. All storage crates allow access to the same items for that player.)

item_13461.Description: A box for storing up to 16 items. Lasts for 5 minutes once deployed. (Each player that access the storage crate can store their own items. All storage crates allow access to the same items for that player.)
item_13461.Name: Awesome Storage Crate

item_13481.Description: A small cask used in dairy food production.
item_13481.Name: Firkin

item_13482.Description: A mid-sized cask used for food and drink production.
item_13482.Name: Kilderkin

item_13483.Description: A large cask used for storing wet and dry goods.
item_13483.Name: Barrel

item_13501.Description: An elaborate contraption that can dispense free items. This model can dispense up to 10 of a single kind of item.
item_13501.Name: Simple Item Dispenser

item_13502.Description: An elaborate contraption that can dispense free items. This model can dispense up to 1000 of a single kind of item.
item_13502.Name: Large-Capacity Item Dispenser

item_13503.Description: An elaborate contraption that can dispense free items. This model can dispense up to 1000 of a single kind of item and has a place for a custom message that all visitors will see.
item_13503.Name: Fancy Item Dispenser

item_13513.Description: An elaborate contraption that can dispense items and collect currency. This model can sell up to 10 of a single kind of item.
item_13513.Name: Simple Item Vendor

item_13514.Description: An elaborate contraption that can dispense items and collect currency. This model can sell up to 1000 of a single kind of item.
item_13514.Name: Large-Capacity Item Vendor

item_13515.Description: An elaborate contraption that can dispense items and collect currency. This model can sell up to 1000 of a single kind of item and has a place for a custom message that all users will see.
item_13515.Name: Fancy Item Vendor

item_13521.Description:
An elaborate contraption that can dispense free raffle tickets and then deliver a reward to the raffle winner.

This model can dispense up to 10 free raffle tickets for a single item (or item stack).
item_13521.Name: Simple Free Item Raffler

item_14001.Description: A simple wooden key with a faint green magical glow.
item_14001.Name: Wooden Key

item_14002.Description: A key cut from magical ice. It won't melt until it is used in whatever strange door it's designed for.
item_14002.Name: Winter Nexus Key

item_14003.Description:
A brief note written in a lovely flowing script. It says,

"Do you remember when your helm was shattered? Probably not. You gave it to me to repair, but it was beyond my skill. I took it to Haetrix, who used inappropriately-strong magic, and now its reality is damaged. Anyway, if your helm disappears in a puff of logic, don't fret. I've locked it in a box for you near the Sun Vale mouth. Gut a troll to light the lamp light, rip the wings off a deviant fae for the second, and rip out the stomach of your least favorite ogre for the third.

- Trallix"
item_14003.Name: Note to Algid Overseer Winterhue

item_14004.Description: A key cut from magical ice.
item_14004.Name: Dementia Puck's Key

item_14005.Description: A key formed of dirt, held in place via magic.
item_14005.Name: Fae Animal Nexus Key

item_14006.Description: It's a piece of lacquered wood shaped like a long worm with a fanged mouth. Pretty impressive, really.
item_14006.Name: Gulagra's Sigil Key

item_14007.Description: It's a small parchment with a magical inscription. You can use this to get past a huge icy barrier beneath the ruined tower in Kur.
item_14007.Name: Ice Bypass Spell

item_14008.Description: A small metal key you found in a cave in Kur Mountains.
item_14008.Name: Wolf Loot Key

item_14009.Description: A metal key from Gravamux, a ghoul.
item_14009.Name: Gravamux's Key

item_14010.Description: A crystal used to unlock certain Crone Hegemony armory chests. This one is partially digested, but should still work.
item_14010.Name: Hegemonic Storage Key

item_14011.Description: An ancient stone key, worn by yetis as a good luck token.
item_14011.Name: Yeti Key

item_14012.Description:
A note in a jaggy, hurried handwriting. It says,

"Test is still underway. I have passed the Combat and Teleportation trials, but I can't figure out how to get into the locked chest with the altars around it. I used Divination, but the only answer I got was 'SEWN'.

I still have my secret weapon: a Potion of Brilliance. Will drink it if necessary, but leaving it here for now."

item_14013.Description:
A metal key with a note attached. In flowery script it says,

"My dear Lawyr, I knew you could do it! Meet me on the mainland and I'll help you recover your destiny. - Yurra"

item_18021.Description:
This particular piece of fluorite is blue with pink bands. Used in magic, it helps you communicate with animals. It also focuses the mind inwards.

Associated Primary Skill: Animal Handling
Associated Secondary Skill: Meditation
item_18021.Name: Fluorite

item_18022.Description:
It's a small peridot, mint green in color. Used in magic, it wards off distracting thoughts and helps align your accuracy.

Associated Primary Skill: Archery
Associated Secondary Skill: Calligraphy
item_18022.Name: Peridot

item_18023.Description:
A small crystal made up of black and white bands. Used in magic, it guards against physical dangers.

Associated Primary Skill: Shield
Associated Secondary Skills: Armor Patching, Tanning, Leatherworking
item_18023.Name: Onyx

item_18024.Description:
This small gem is brownish orange. Used in magic, it provides extra courage or energy to someone under great stress.

Associated Primary Skill: Axe
Associated Secondary Skill: Tailoring
item_18024.Name: Sardonyx

item_18025.Description:
A small orange gem with many magical uses. Humans appreciate it for its ability to reduce anxiety.

Associated Primary Skill: Battle Chemistry
item_18025.Name: Citrine

item_18026.Description:
A pretty gem with dark green bands, it's well known for aiding magical communication.

Associated Primary Skills: Cow, Pig, Deer, Spider
item_18026.Name: Malachite

item_18027.Description:
A small piece of white quartz. High-quality pieces like this one can amplify elemental magic.

Associated Primary Skill: Fire Magic
item_18027.Name: Quartz

item_18028.Description:
A dark red stone, known for its curative properties.

Associated Primary Skill: Druid

Associated Secondary Skill: First Aid
item_18028.Name: Garnet

item_18029.Description:
A small gem, light blue-green in color. It's a traditional protective stone for fishermen.

Associated Primary Skill: Fishing
Associated Secondary Skill: Teleportation
item_18029.Name: Aquamarine

item_18030.Description:
A small black stone. Knives that incorporate obsidian can be enchanted more thoroughly than regular blades.

Associated Primary Skill: Knives
Associated Secondary Skill: Toolcrafting
item_18030.Name: Obsidian

item_18031.Description:
A white stone with dark green veins, the moss agate is also known as the Gardener's Talisman.

Associated Primary Skill: Hammer

Associated Secondary Skills: Gardening, Mycology
item_18031.Name: Moss Agate

item_18032.Description:
A small yellow topaz. An incredibly versatile magical stone.

Associated Primary Skill: Mentalism
item_18032.Name: Topaz

item_18033.Description:
A purple stone, used in magic to facilitate travel.

Associated Primary Skill: Teleportation
item_18033.Name: Amethyst

item_18034.Description:
A lovely dark blue stone, with limited but potent magic uses.

Associated Primary Skill: Staff
item_18034.Name: Blue Spinel

item_18035.Description:
A red gem. Used in magic, it balances the senses and sharpens the mind to imminent danger.

Associated Primary Skill: Sword
item_18035.Name: Carnelian

item_18036.Description:
This banded gem is used in magic to promote grace and give power to the body.

Associated Primary Skill: Unarmed
item_18036.Name: Agate

item_18037.Description:
This gem is dark green with red spots. In magic it is used to command nature.

Associated Primary Skill: Weather Witching
Associated Secondary Skill: Cooking
item_18037.Name: Bloodstone

item_18038.Description:
Milky white, this gem is useful in magic that relates to 'new beginnings.'

Associated Primary Skill: Lycanthropy
item_18038.Name: Moonstone

item_18039.Description:
A soft blue rock. It's useful in curatives and curse removal potions.

Associated Primary Skill: Alchemy
item_18039.Name: Lapis Lazuli

item_18040.Description:
A pretty green gem. Used in magic, it increases comprehension of scientific concepts.

Associated Primary Skill: Ice Magic
Associated Secondary Skill: Geology
item_18040.Name: Tsavorite

item_18041.Description:
A scintillating stone. Used in magic, it can mesmerize and soothe.

Associated Primary Skill: Combat Psychology
item_18041.Name: Tourmaline

item_18042.Description:
A dull yellow-green stone. Used in magic, it can pierce the barrier between life and death.

Associated Primary Skill: Necromancy
item_18042.Name: Serpentine

item_18043.Description: A scintillating gemstone. Used in magic, it can protect against death.
item_18043.Name: Diamond

item_18044.Description: A bright blue stone, almost teal in color. In magic, it is associated with beaches and waves.
item_18044.Name: Turquoise

item_18045.Description: A beautiful blue stone. In magic it is associated with flight and the sky.
item_18045.Name: Sapphire

item_18046.Description: This green crystal is a type of beryl. Used in magic, it is associated with perfection, richness, and deities.
item_18046.Name: Emerald

item_18047.Description: This is an orange variety of beryl. Used in magic, it is associated with tailoring. It is the favored color of goblins.
item_18047.Name: Morganite

item_18048.Description: This pale yellow crystal is extremely reflective from certain angles. In magic, it is associated with growth.
item_18048.Name: Sunstone

item_18049.Description: This beautiful golden rock is has deep striations. In magic, it is associated with animals, hunting, and livestock.
item_18049.Name: Tiger's Eye

item_18050.Description: This greenish stone seems to have many other colors embedded in it. While some find it beautiful, others find it disconcerting or even ugly. In magic it is associated with curses and the evil eye.
item_18050.Name: Opal

item_18051.Description: A clear variety of beryl. It is not particularly powerful in magic, but it can be used as a sort of energy dampener.
item_18051.Name: Goshenite

item_18052.Description: This white gem with purple streaks is exceptionally strong and makes very resilient jewelry. In magic, it is likewise associated with toughness.
item_18052.Name: Danburite

item_18053.Description: Deep crimson in color, this valuable gem is used in magic to ensure good fortune.
item_18053.Name: Ruby

item_18181.Description: A magical diamond that is flowing with fae power.
item_18181.Name: Winterprize

item_18201.Description: A pretty gem with dark green bands, it's well known for aiding magical communication. This particular piece has been infused with a rune that attunes it to cattle when used in crafting.
item_18201.Name: Cow Malachite

item_18202.Description: A pretty gem with dark green bands, it's well known for aiding magical communication. This particular piece has been infused with a rune that attunes it to the needs of deer when used in crafting.
item_18202.Name: Deer Malachite

item_18203.Description: A pretty gem with dark green bands, it's well known for aiding magical communication. This particular piece has been infused with a rune that attunes it to pigs when used in crafting.
item_18203.Name: Pig Malachite

item_18204.Description: A pretty gem with dark green bands, it's well known for aiding magical communication. This particular piece has been infused with a rune that attunes it to spiders when used in crafting.
item_18204.Name: Spider Malachite

item_18205.Description: A dark red stone, known for its curative properties. This particular stone has been attuned to the First Aid skill if used in crafting.
item_18205.Name: First Aid Garnet

item_18206.Description: A small crystal made up of black and white bands. Used in magic, it guards against physical dangers. This particular onyx has been attuned to Armor Patching when used in crafting.
item_18206.Name: Armor Patching Onyx

item_18207.Description: A pretty gem with dark green bands, it's well known for aiding magical communication. This particular piece has been infused with a rune that attunes it to bats when used in crafting.
item_18207.Name: Bat Malachite

item_18301.Description: This small gem is brownish orange. It has been tuned as an amplifier for certain tailoring recipes.
item_18301.Name: Maximized Sardonyx

item_18302.Description: A small crystal made up of black and white bands. This particular gem has been tuned to act as an amplifier for certain leatherworking recipes.
item_18302.Name: Maximized Onyx

item_18303.Description: A small black stone. It has been tuned as an amplifier for certain toolcrafting recipes.
item_18303.Name: Maximized Obsidian

item_18304.Description: A blue-green stone. It has been tuned as an amplifier for certain armorsmithing recipes.
item_18304.Name: Maximized Aquamarine

item_19001.Description: Rita asked you to deliver this soap to Helena, who lives in the ruins of Castle Eltibule.
item_19001.Name: Herbal Soap

item_19002.Description: This bean has little prongs growing out of it that kind of look like horns.
item_19002.Name: Demon Bean

item_19003.Description: A rooty vegetable heart. Would probably be great in a salad.
item_19003.Name: Salmpo Heart

item_19005.Description: A small sack of foul-smelling white dust. Echur instructed you not to eat it, but that shouldn't be a problem.
item_19005.Name: Unrefined Cranium Powder

item_19006.Description: A handful of odorous twinkling flowers. Cute, but a little too gimmicky.
item_19006.Name: Flitterbies

item_19007.Description: A pack full of extremely small woman's clothing, plus blankets and some costume jewelry.
item_19007.Name: Sarina's Backpack

item_19008.Description: A grisly paw hacked off of The Mauler.
item_19008.Name: The Mauler's Claw

item_19010.Description: Mu asked you to deliver this to a Myconian named Poe.
item_19010.Name: Mu's Message Spore

item_19012.Description: This bundle of sporelings should be delivered to a myconian named Yoy.
item_19012.Name: Backup Sporelings

item_19013.Description: It's a partially-acid-melted shield without any straps to keep it on.
item_19013.Name: Melted and Broken Shield

item_19014.Description: It's a note to Landri the Cold, an elf in Kur Mountains. It reads, "You have not met me, and I cannot reveal myself, but I am a fellow theoretician, and I beg your help. I believe I can tap a portal to other planes of existence, and the plane of ice is very accessible here. I intend to use the Galkun technique to open the wormhole, and power it via ordinary ice lichen." (The note goes on for some length, in increasing technical detail, before ending with a perfunctory request for verification of the plan.)
item_19014.Name: Letter to Landri the Cold

item_19015.Description: A lead cup with a hefty weight and some cheap jewels on it. As you hold it, it grows unnaturally warm to the touch.
item_19015.Name: Necromancer's Goblet

item_19016.Description: A chunk of a weird giant mushroom. It reeks of death, and you're pretty sure it has no practical use.
item_19016.Name: Giant Mushroom Sample

item_19017.Description: A small poorly-made tiara, sized for a large rat or smallish dog. It seems utterly non-magical.
item_19017.Name: Squeaky's Tiara

item_19018.Description: It's an official letter from Praetor Ballard, demanding that a Human named Charles Thompson leave Serbule's surroundings forever... or face death.
item_19018.Name: Praetor's Orders

item_19020.Description: A sack of millet from a strange plant.
item_19020.Name: Gratflower Millet

item_19021.Description: A rakshasa's tail ring. It's not magical. It is inscribed, "to Sinda, the explorer supreme."
item_19021.Name: Sinda's Tail Ring

item_19022.Description: A sage's personal diary. It doesn't contain any useful lore or anything, it's just ramblings about his personal life.
item_19022.Name: Journal of Sir Villas Wake

item_19023.Description: A lovely navel ring with a tourmaline in it, apparently designed to calm intense anger.
item_19023.Name: Oritania's Navel Ring

item_19024.Description: The skull of a dead necromancer.
item_19024.Name: Lomas's Skull

item_19025.Description: A large gear that came out of a very large golem. It's bent and has no obvious purpose.
item_19025.Name: Cranial Gear

item_19026.Description: A small piece of bone inscribed with a dwarven rune for eternal sleep. It doesn't look very useful to you.
item_19026.Name: Preservative Rune

item_19027.Description: The skull of a ghoul that invaded from a realm of evil.
item_19027.Name: Skull of Maligno

item_19028.Description: A prism that has been inscribed with weird symbols. You don't think it would be useful for regular prism-related activities.
item_19028.Name: Archaic Prism

item_19029.Description: It's an old note. "Relamir: if you read this, get out of here! The frog men came again... and they killed the guests and staff. There's nobody left but me, and I'm leaving. Fuck this island, fuck this whole inn idea, fuck money, fuck the ocean, fuck everything. I'll pay you the money I owe you within a decade, I promise. - Roolaustus"
item_19029.Name: Old Owner's Note

item_22001.Description: A chunk of ore that could be used to make silver equipment and jewelry. It can also be used in formulas that augment jewelry.
item_22001.Name: Silver Ore

item_22002.Description: A chunk of fool's gold. It has many alchemical uses, and is great for making costume jewelry. It is often used in formulas that augment jewelry.
item_22002.Name: Pyrite

item_22003.Description: A chunk of ore that could be used to make gold equipment and jewelry. It is also used in formulas that augment jewelry.
item_22003.Name: Gold Ore

item_22004.Description: A chunk of dense (yet brittle) iridium. It's used in the creation of acid-proof armor and strange robotic constructs. It can also be used to augment jewelry.
item_22004.Name: Iridium

item_22005.Description: A tiny bit of unrefined ore. You'd need a bunch of these to make anything useful from them.
item_22005.Name: Gold Nugget

item_22006.Description: A chunk of weird ore. It's a potent conductor of certain magics and is used in specialized armor and weapons.
item_22006.Name: Paladium

item_22007.Description: A chink of brittle ore. It is extremely hard to smith, but alchemists have found some uses for it.
item_22007.Name: Tungsten

item_22008.Description: A chunk of soft metal. While it's not particularly strong, it's very easy for smiths to work with, so it has uses in specialized armors and weapons. Fletchers use it to create dense arrows.
item_22008.Name: Copper Ore

item_22009.Description: A soft strange metal, quite magical, and very poisonous. It has many uses.
item_22009.Name: Cinnabar

item_22010.Description: A chunk of pointy ore. Its most common use is by blacksmiths, who can add fireproofing to armor with it.
item_22010.Name: Stibnite

item_22011.Description: A chunk of weird ore that can conduct powerful magics, but requires extreme skill to craft with.
item_22011.Name: Rhodium
