item_40002.Description: Sturdy and fashionable, if not especially protective.
item_40002.Name: Basic Boots

item_40003.Description: These have been perfectly worn in! Nice. But still very smelly.
item_40003.Name: Comfortable Ancient Shoes

item_40005.Description: These boots have been hand-painted, but are still pretty ugly.
item_40005.Name: Sturdy Boots

item_40006.Description: These were worn by a dainty goblin.
item_40006.Name: Goblin Slippers

item_40007.Description: These were worn by a tough goblin.
item_40007.Name: Goblin Stompers

item_40010.Description: When you put these slippers on, your whole body feels lighter.
item_40010.Name: Featherweights

item_40011.Description: These boots have been dyed red and given a preposterous name.
item_40011.Name: Hateboots

item_40013.Description: Strong general-purpose footwear, with metal outside for protection, wool inside for insulation.
item_40013.Name: Ruggedized Boots

item_40015.Description: Handmade by a fairy, these make you especially light on your feet.
item_40015.Name: Flower Dainties

item_40017.Description: Horseshoes, but fitted for a cow's hooves.
item_40017.Name: Cow Shoes

item_40018.Description: Horseshoes, but fitted for a pig's hooves.
item_40018.Name: Pig Shoes

item_40019.Description: A pair of simple boots. Echur says that they help one connect with the world around them, whatever that means.
item_40019.Name: Echur's Boots

item_40020.Description: Horseshoes, but fitted for a deer's hooves.
item_40020.Name: Deer Shoes

item_40021.Description: These boots are abysmal, leaky, and humiliating to wear.
item_40021.Name: Shoddy Leather Boots

item_40022.Description: Well, they're hand-made shoes. Not everything that's hand-made is good quality, though, it turns out.
item_40022.Name: Rough Leather Boots

item_40023.Description: Hideous foot wrappings covered in excess leather to provide protection – but not comfort. Expect gigantic blisters.
item_40023.Name: Crude Leather Boots

item_40024.Description: The sort of boots you might imagine if you tried to visualize leather boots in your head. Fairly generic.
item_40024.Name: Decent Leather Boots

item_40025.Description: Boots with a fair amount of reinforcement in the heel, and padding to prevent blisters. Still not elegant, but fairly effective in combat.
item_40025.Name: Nice Leather Boots

item_40026.Description: These boots are pretty nice to wear, and seem like they'll last a long time, too.
item_40026.Name: Quality Leather Boots

item_40027.Description: These are so soft to touch that you almost feel criminal wearing them out into the mud and gore.
item_40027.Name: Great Leather Boots

item_40028.Description: These boots breathe better than most leather garments, so your feet don't get quite as stinky. Plus, they have double-reinforced laces!
item_40028.Name: Amazing Leather Boots

item_40029.Description: This shoe has been heavily over-engineered, with secret cushions and odd snaps to ensure a perfect fit for any foot size.
item_40029.Name: Astounding Leather Boots

item_40030.Description: These are like an extension of your feet, they're so comfortable!
item_40030.Name: Awesome Leather Boots

item_40041.Description: Farmers typically don't feel compelled to shod a cow. But some cows are more violent and adventurous than others.
item_40041.Name: Shoddy Cow Shoes

item_40042.Description: Your violent cow will be made all the more violent by these uncomfortable shoes!
item_40042.Name: Rough Cow Shoes

item_40043.Description: A crude cow will love these crude shoes.
item_40043.Name: Crude Cow Shoes

item_40044.Description: Decent shoes for a cow that's not too shabby.
item_40044.Name: Decent Cow Shoes

item_40045.Description: Comfortable shoes that make a violent cow feel free as the wind.
item_40045.Name: Nice Cow Shoes

item_40048.Description: These horseshoes – err, cow shoes – are practically supernaturally lovely.
item_40048.Name: Amazing Cow Shoes

item_40049.Description: Wow, someone put way too much effort into these cow shoes!
item_40049.Name: Astounding Cow Shoes

item_40050.Description: If you know anything about cowshoe craftsmanship, you know you're looking at a masterpiece right here.
item_40050.Name: Awesome Cow Shoes

item_40061.Description: Deer seem to get along fine in nature without having metal hammered into their hooves, but not all deer are content with the life of a passive ungulate.
item_40061.Name: Shoddy Deer Shoes

item_40062.Description: The nails are too long for the deer's small hooves, causing considerable pain while wearing.
item_40062.Name: Rough Deer Shoes

item_40063.Description: A crude deer will love these crude shoes.
item_40063.Name: Crude Deer Shoes

item_40064.Description: Decent shoes for a deer that's not too shabby.
item_40064.Name: Decent Deer Shoes

item_40065.Description: Comfortable shoes that make a violent deer feel free as the wind.
item_40065.Name: Nice Deer Shoes

item_40068.Description: These horseshoes – err, deer shoes – are practically supernaturally lovely.
item_40068.Name: Amazing Deer Shoes

item_40069.Description: Wow, someone put way too much effort into these deer shoes!
item_40069.Name: Astounding Deer Shoes

item_40070.Description: If you know anything about deershoe craftsmanship, you know you're looking at a masterpiece right here.
item_40070.Name: Awesome Deer Shoes

item_40071.Description: If a cow needed to be shod for some reason, it is surely not with these wooden, splinter-laced bits of junk.
item_40071.Name: Shoddy Wooden Cow Shoes

item_40072.Description: Basically just chunks of wood nailed to a cow's feet. Which makes them sound more comfortable than they really are.
item_40072.Name: Rough Wooden Cow Shoes

item_40073.Description: Not generally considered a good choice, shodding a cow with bits of wood. These crude shoes are... crude.
item_40073.Name: Crude Wooden Cow Shoes

item_40074.Description: If all you're looking for is some horseshoe-shaped pieces of wood to nail to your cow's feet, you're in luck.
item_40074.Name: Decent Wooden Cow Shoes

item_40075.Description: Elegantly whittled and reinforced wooden shoes. They can easily withstand the weight of an angry heiffer.
item_40075.Name: Nice Wooden Cow Shoes

item_40076.Description: Made by someone with decent working knowledge of wood, these seem fairly comfortable if you have hooves for feet.
item_40076.Name: Quality Wooden Cow Shoes

item_40077.Description: You'd almost think these were metal, that's how great these bits of wood are!
item_40077.Name: Great Wooden Cow Shoes

item_40078.Description: These wooden footguards are a work of art. Avant garde art, where you nail wood to cows' feet.
item_40078.Name: Amazing Wooden Cow Shoes

item_40079.Description: Wow, someone put way too much effort into these wooden cow shoes!
item_40079.Name: Astounding Wooden Cow Shoes

item_40080.Description: A masterpiece of wood-nailed-to-cow-hoof design! Comfortable and stylish. Well, stylish for a cow. They have different sensibilities than people.
item_40080.Name: Awesome Wooden Cow Shoes

item_40081.Description: If a deer needed to be shod for some reason, it is surely not with these wooden, splinter-laced bits of junk.
item_40081.Name: Shoddy Wooden Deer Shoes

item_40082.Description: Basically just chunks of wood nailed to a deer's feet. Which makes them sound more comfortable than they really are.
item_40082.Name: Rough Wooden Deer Shoes

item_40083.Description: Not generally considered a good choice, shodding a deer with bits of wood. These crude shoes are... crude.
item_40083.Name: Crude Wooden Deer Shoes

item_40084.Description: If all you're looking for is some horseshoe-shaped pieces of wood to nail to your deer's feet, you're in luck.
item_40084.Name: Decent Wooden Deer Shoes

item_40085.Description: Elegantly whittled and reinforced wooden shoes. They can easily withstand the weight of an angry buck.
item_40085.Name: Nice Wooden Deer Shoes

item_40086.Description: Made by someone with decent working knowledge of wood, these seem fairly comfortable if you have hooves for feet.
item_40086.Name: Quality Wooden Deer Shoes

item_40087.Description: You'd almost think these were metal, that's how great these bits of wood are!
item_40087.Name: Great Wooden Deer Shoes

item_40088.Description: These wooden footguards are a work of art. Avant garde art, where you nail wood to the feet of an unsuspecting ungulate.
item_40088.Name: Amazing Wooden Deer Shoes

item_40089.Description: Wow, someone put way too much effort into these wooden deer shoes!
item_40089.Name: Astounding Wooden Deer Shoes

item_40090.Description: A masterpiece of wood-nailed-to-deer-hoof design! Comfortable and stylish. Well, stylish for a deer. They have different sensibilities than people.
item_40090.Name: Awesome Wooden Deer Shoes

item_40101.Description: Special deer-fitted horseshoes made of an otherworldly metal.
item_40101.Name: Shadow Trotters

item_40102.Description: Thick layers of hide and fur make these boots quite warm.
item_40102.Name: Insulated Boots

item_40103.Description: Although they're leather instead of metal, these insulated boots are made for protection, not grace or mobility.
item_40103.Name: Orcish Rugged Boots

item_40104.Description: It's hard to imagine, but once these boots were the height of fashion.
item_40104.Name: Discarded Boots

item_40105.Description: These fancy boots have been digested by a slime creature, leaving mostly just metal behind. Don't worry about them being uncomfortable, though: there's tons of ooze in there to keep your feet cozy.
item_40105.Name: Slimy Shoes

item_40106.Description: These boots have clearly been the birthing spot for baby spiders in the past. You can clean them off, but can you ever really get the image out of your head?
item_40106.Name: Web-Encrusted Shoes

item_40107.Description: A werewolf wore these boots while transforming a few too many times. The armor quality is totally shot, but it still has some value.
item_40107.Name: Ruined Shifter's Boots

item_40109.Description: Profoundly uncomfortable and rather awkward to move in, but very stylish.
item_40109.Name: Elven Plate Boots

item_40110.Description: Made of a bizarre metal, these uncomfortable boots seem to clench your feet with malice.
item_40110.Name: Boots of the Winter Court

item_40111.Description: Common apparel from the Serbule Revolt, 1500 years ago. These boots are so over-engineered that they look brand new. But the smell is pretty bad.
item_40111.Name: Dwarven Soldier Boots

item_40112.Description: The evil creature Ciervos wore these for thousands of years. Must be lucky! Hmm, but he died wearing them. Maybe they're unlucky...
item_40112.Name: Ciervos's Anklets

item_40113.Description: Makeshift fae armor crafted from repurposed Winter Court armor. It doesn't have quite the style or powers of Summer Court armor, but it's not bad.
item_40113.Name: Boots of the Summer Court

item_40114.Description: Designed by a spiteful necromancer bent on conquering a city, these cloth foot coverings seethe with hatred. And it turns out that pure hatred is pretty warm, providing mild protection against the cold.
item_40114.Name: Booties of Hateful Comeuppance

item_40115.Description: When thousands of Rakshasa warriors arrived on Alharth, they wore boots like these, designed to accommodate all environments. The secret to their crafting is lost to the Rakshasa living here now.
item_40115.Name: Ravana Soldier Boots

item_40116.Description: Popular with elven messengers, these elegant cloth footwraps make your feet move much faster! But they don't protect your feet very well, so you'll need significant endurance to tolerate the numerous stubbed toes and sprained ankles.
item_40116.Name: Windstep Shoes

item_40117.Description: Sturdy and fashionable, if not especially protective.
item_40117.Name: Basic Boots

item_40118.Description: These boots have been hand-painted, but are still pretty ugly.
item_40118.Name: Sturdy Boots

item_40120.Description: A bit of leaves, a bit of bark, and a lot of magic.
item_40120.Name: Spring Fairy Shoes

item_40121.Description: Part of the ancient uniform of Dwarven Stalwarts, the elite warriors entrusted with protecting the most important Dwarven secrets. Quality-wise, they're very protective, but very uncomfortable.
item_40121.Name: Stalwart Boots

item_40122.Description: A pair of old cloth shoes that are much, much tougher than they look.
item_40122.Name: Tough Old Shoes

item_40123.Description: These are shoddy boots that have had sections of their protective armor removed to make them a little more agile. The holes let moisture in, and they quickly stink beyond fathoming.
item_40123.Name: Crude Evasion Boots

item_40124.Description: Reasonable boots that have been oiled and softened to let the wearer dash and dart about. Kinda comfortable, but not really.
item_40124.Name: Decent Evasion Boots

item_40125.Description: Someone with competence put together these nimble leather boots. Only a small amount of protection is lost in exchange for nimble dodging ability.
item_40125.Name: Nice Evasion Boots

item_40126.Description: Quality stuff! These are the sort of evasion boots you'd see in a storefront window, if there was a store specifically for evasion boots, which there is not.
item_40126.Name: Quality Evasion Boots

item_40151.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew. The sinews were not properly cured and stink beyond comprehension.
item_40151.Name: Decent Snail Boots

item_40152.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew. Only somewhat stinky.
item_40152.Name: Nice Snail Boots

item_40153.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew.
item_40153.Name: Quality Snail Boots

item_40154.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew.
item_40154.Name: Great Snail Boots

item_40155.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew.
item_40155.Name: Amazing Snail Boots

item_40156.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew.
item_40156.Name: Astounding Snail Boots

item_40157.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew.
item_40157.Name: Awesome Snail Boots

item_40201.Description: A bit of leaves, a bit of bark, and a lot of magic.
item_40201.Name: Nice Spring Fairy Shoes

item_40202.Description: A bit of leaves, a bit of bark, and a lot of magic.
item_40202.Name: Quality Spring Fairy Shoes

item_40203.Description: A bit of leaves, a bit of bark, and a lot of magic.
item_40203.Name: Great Spring Fairy Shoes

item_40221.Description: Simple bits of metal designed to fit on the hind legs of a wolf.
item_40221.Name: Shoddy Werewolf Hind Leg Guards

item_40222.Description: Simple bits of metal designed to fit on the hind legs of a wolf.
item_40222.Name: Rough Werewolf Hind Leg Guards

item_40223.Description: Simple bits of metal designed to fit on the hind legs of a wolf.
item_40223.Name: Crude Werewolf Hind Leg Guards

item_40224.Description: Resilient metal guards for a wolf's hind legs.
item_40224.Name: Decent Werewolf Hind Leg Guards

item_40225.Description: Resilient metal guards for a wolf's hind legs.
item_40225.Name: Nice Werewolf Hind Leg Guards

item_40226.Description: Resilient metal guards for a wolf's hind legs.
item_40226.Name: Quality Werewolf Hind Leg Guards

item_40227.Description: Resilient metal guards for a wolf's hind legs.
item_40227.Name: Great Werewolf Hind Leg Guards

item_40228.Description: Resilient metal guards for a wolf's hind legs.
item_40228.Name: Amazing Werewolf Hind Leg Guards

item_40229.Description: Resilient metal guards for a wolf's hind legs.
item_40229.Name: Astounding Werewolf Hind Leg Guards

item_40230.Description: Resilient metal guards for a wolf's hind legs.
item_40230.Name: Awesome Werewolf Hind Leg Guards

item_40301.Description: Worn leather boots with metal meticulously inserted into them. Whoever made these lacked skill in leatherworking, but made up for it with time and attention to detail.
item_40301.Name: Desert Vagabond Boots

item_40302.Description: This is the latest masterpiece of rakshasa leatherworking, designed to replace the old Ravana armor they can no longer create. In many ways, this surpasses anything from their homeworld, a testament to rakshasa skill... and the toughness of beasts in Alharth.
item_40302.Name: Rakshasian Elite Boots

item_40303.Description: Thick matted hair combined with spider silk. These feel great. No, really. They don't look great, but they feel great.
item_40303.Name: Yeti Stockings

item_40304.Description: Sturdy and fashionable, if not especially protective.
item_40304.Name: Basic Boots

item_40305.Description: Thick layers of hide and fur make these boots quite warm.
item_40305.Name: Insulated Boots

item_40306.Description: The isolated elf colony of Sedgewick Forest prefers armor of this type because it reminds them of their home in Verta. It's been explained to them that nobody in Verta dresses this way anymore, but they don't seem to care.
item_40306.Name: Thentree Boots

item_40307.Description: Made of a bizarre metal, these uncomfortable boots seem to clench your feet with malice.
item_40307.Name: Great Boots of the Winter Court

item_40308.Description: Used by the typical troops of the Crone Hegemony.
item_40308.Name: Peltast Boots

item_40309.Description: The evil necromancer/mentalist wore these comfy booties whenever he destroyed towns or villages.
item_40309.Name: Mortimer's Booties

item_40310.Description: "To my lover, may she run back to me soon. - Raul"
item_40310.Name: Hooves of the Inamorata

item_40311.Description: Made of insanely strong scorpion and beetle carapace plates riveted together, these boots will keep your feet safe from everything except blisters. It's a pity carapace plates aren't more comfortable...
EffectDescs: You reflect 4% of any physical attack damage (Slashing, Piercing, or Crushing) back at the attacker.
item_40311.Name: Scorpiclaw Boots

item_40312.Description: The customized scorpiclaw boots of the dread Ankara general. They fit a little better than normal.
EffectDescs: You reflect 4% of any physical attack damage (Slashing, Piercing, or Crushing) back at the attacker.
item_40312.Name: General Pask's Boots

item_40313.Description: Budget-conscious goblins love these boots, which look as sturdy as regular goblin boots, but a fraction of the cost!
item_40313.Name: Cheap Goblin Boots

item_41001.Description: These have been in the muck for ages...
item_41001.Name: Moldy Ancient Pants

item_41002.Description: Nice greaves. Vaguely stylish yet vaguely protective.
item_41002.Name: Basic Pants

item_41003.Description: Sure they're gross, but they're already worn in, and the caked-on dirt provides extra resilience.
item_41003.Name: Comfortable Ancient Pants

item_41004.Description: Comfy, invigorating, and magically protective. They smell like lilac and pimentos for some reason.
item_41004.Name: Rita's Lucky Underpants

item_41005.Description: Gold! With little white frill things. Reasonably protective, too.
item_41005.Name: Sturdy Pants

item_41006.Description: A protective garment that also keeps you light on your feet. The goblin smell, unfortunately, doesn't wash out.
item_41006.Name: Goblin Skirt

item_41007.Description: Strong pants made of leather. You don't want to think about what creature the leather may have come from.
item_41007.Name: Goblin Leggings

item_41008.Description: Made from the skin of abominations, these pants seem to constantly fondle your legs as you wear them. It's really quite disturbing, but the armor is tough...
item_41008.Name: Nightmare Pants

item_41009.Description: The "quality" in the title refers to the defensive merits, not the fashion statement.
item_41009.Name: Quality Pants

item_41011.Description: Crafted by elves who were too homesick to get out of bed, the Pants of the Yearning Sea are sorrow incarnate. But these sure are comfy. Plus, the tears that dripped onto the fabric have made it extra bouncy!
item_41011.Name: Pants of the Yearning Sea

item_41012.Description: Once worn by Makopa the semi-legendary goblin boss.
item_41012.Name: Makopa's Pants

item_41013.Description: They're supernaturally slimming! Plus they have a hidden dimensional pocket inside that can fit a few extra items.
item_41013.Name: Rita's Disturbing Dimensional Panties

item_41014.Description: Created by an alchemist/farmer to protect her legs in the fields, these pants are great at keeping nature off of you. Too bad about the odor...
item_41014.Name: Ivyn's Family Pants

item_41015.Description: Full of wool! Way too much wool. You'd get heatstroke if it was too hot!
item_41015.Name: Ukorga's Experimental Pants

item_41016.Description: These once-amazing pants aren't amazing anymore. They're torn and mangled. But there's still some armor on them... could be worse! A hand-sewn tag inside says "To General Lawyr, may you remember me always, your Kello."
item_41016.Name: General Lawyr's Pants

item_41020.Description: Apparently Rita gave these to Sir Coth, who has since discarded them.
item_41020.Name: Sir Coth's Discarded Gift

item_41021.Description: Somebody has worn these undergarments previously without washing them. Hopefully that person was you. But you're not sure. Anyway, they reek, plus they provide no armor.
item_41021.Name: Crude Underwear

item_41022.Description: Someone was buried in these, apparently. They're caked with dust, but don't seem the worse for wear.
item_41022.Name: Ancient Slacks

item_41023.Description: Any beauty these leggings once possessed has long faded. But they still have an inner beauty, right?
item_41023.Name: Long-Lost Leggings

item_41024.Description: There's a big hole in these, but a decade of spiderweb build-up kind of seals the hole. Kind of.
item_41024.Name: Web-Encrusted Pants

item_41025.Description: These cotton undergarments are possibly the least interesting piece of clothing possible.
item_41025.Name: Cotton Long Underwear

item_41026.Description: These are just cotton underclothes, but they're really well made!
item_41026.Name: Long Stockings

item_41027.Description: Leather armor with a thin layer of strong metal inside.
item_41027.Name: Orcish Greaves

item_41028.Description: During the Elf-Dwarf wars, Dwarven mages created leather-evaporation magic, rendering elves' usual armor obsolete. These ceremonial plate leggings were hurried into battle. Although they're impressively protective, they're still pretty uncomfortable.
item_41028.Name: Elven Plate Leggings

item_41029.Description: The metal is always freezing cold, but you'll soon become numb to such trivial irritations.
item_41029.Name: Greaves of the Winter Court

item_41030.Description: It's been about 15 centuries since the Serbule Revolt, but these dwarven leggings don't seem a day over 450. Their preservative magic is quite strong.
item_41030.Name: Dwarven Soldier Leggings

item_41031.Description: Made from repurposed Winter Court armor in an imperfect process. This somehow conveys the warmth of summer while still being quite cold to the touch.
item_41031.Name: Greaves of the Summer Court

item_41032.Description: Designed by a spiteful necromancer bent on conquering a city, these airy pants seethe with hatred. And it turns out that pure hatred is pretty warm, providing mild protection against the cold.
item_41032.Name: Pants of Hateful Comeuppance

item_41033.Description: When thousands of Rakshasa warriors arrived on Alharth, they wore suits of armor like this, designed to accommodate all environments. The secret to their crafting is lost to the Rakshasa living here now.
item_41033.Name: Ravana Soldier Leggings

item_41034.Description: This kilt is part of the uniform of the dwarven Idealist's Guild. Members produce a substance they call "optimism", which is sold in the form of addictive crystals.
item_41034.Name: Idealist's Skirts

item_41035.Description: Nice greaves. Vaguely stylish yet vaguely protective.
item_41035.Name: Basic Pants

item_41036.Description: Gold! With little white frill things. Reasonably protective, too.
item_41036.Name: Sturdy Pants

item_41037.Description: The "quality" in the title refers to the defensive merits, not the fashion statement.
item_41037.Name: Quality Pants

item_41038.Description: Kind of revealing. But very comfortable.
item_41038.Name: Spring Fairy Leggings

item_41039.Description: Dwarven Stalwarts wore leg armor like this a thousand years ago, and then handed down for centuries after the Stalwarts were no more, because these pants are great at absorbing punishment.
item_41039.Name: Stalwart Leggings

item_41040.Description: Made of a bizarre metal, these uncomfortable boots seem to clench your feet with malice.
item_41040.Name: Great Greaves of the Winter Court

item_41041.Description: With horrid stitching and gigantic holes, these smelly pants are just plain sad.
item_41041.Name: Shoddy Leather Leggings

item_41042.Description: Sewn by an amateur, with low-quality materials and a lack of fashion sense.
item_41042.Name: Rough Leather Leggings

item_41043.Description: With an eye toward performance over elegance, these leather pants will protect you from monsters, but not from chafing.
item_41043.Name: Crude Leather Leggings

item_41044.Description: Thanks to a modicum of padding inside, wearing these pants will only leave you severely chafed, instead of incapacitated.
item_41044.Name: Decent Leather Leggings

item_41045.Description: Someone with a basic sense of style has fashioned these leather pants. Unfortunately the protective reinforcement ruins the look, but it could be worse.
item_41045.Name: Nice Leather Leggings

item_41047.Description: Astonishingly, these leather pants don't chafe! This is some high-grade magic right here. Or just great tailoring.
item_41047.Name: Great Leather Leggings

item_41048.Description: These beautiful leather pants are so soft, you just want to pet them. Don't let anybody see you doing that.
item_41048.Name: Amazing Leather Leggings

item_41049.Description: You get the feeling that, even when they were brand new, these pants already had that great worn-in feeling. The padding is strong but not bulky and the leather smell is intoxicating.
item_41049.Name: Astounding Leather Leggings

item_41050.Description: Slip into these and enjoy having leather on your crotch like never before.
item_41050.Name: Awesome Leather Leggings

item_41063.Description: A sub-par pair of leather leggings has been chopped inexpertly to make it more evasive. The result is humiliating in most respects.
item_41063.Name: Crude Evasion Pants

item_41064.Description: These leather pants have had the joints replaced with super-soft leather. The stitching is poor, though, and the pants are drafty. Drafty pants!
item_41064.Name: Decent Evasion Pants

item_41065.Description: These leather pants are so soft. They're nice for dodging arrows and the like.
item_41065.Name: Nice Evasion Pants

item_41066.Description: Stylish, highly mobile, and almost-but-not-quite comfortable leather pants.
item_41066.Name: Quality Evasion Pants

item_41101.Description: A barbaric act of cruelty to cotton.
item_41101.Name: Shoddy Cloth Pants

item_41102.Description: The quadruple-thick stitching screams "overcompensating" and the pattern is frankly horrendous. But it'd be good for sewer-delving or something.
item_41102.Name: Rough Cloth Pants

item_41103.Description: A rustic farmer might consider these pants barely adequate. Might.
item_41103.Name: Crude Cloth Pants

item_41104.Description: The premier choice for those who work the land daily. Strong stitching, and none of that annoying "attractiveness" to get in the way.
item_41104.Name: Decent Cloth Pants

item_41105.Description: Not bad. You wouldn't even be embarrassed to be seen in these nice pants. Unless you were seen by someone you wanted to impress.
item_41105.Name: Nice Cloth Pants

item_41106.Description: Good thread count. Sturdy crotch support. A little stiff, but to be expected for such a resilient pair of pants.
item_41106.Name: Quality Cloth Pants

item_41107.Description: Very soft to the touch, but resistant to damage.
item_41107.Name: Great Cloth Pants

item_41151.Description: Someone has awkwardly painted these sub-par pants. Well, woodland animals aren't super smart, so maybe that'll do.
item_41151.Name: Camouflaged Crude Pants

item_41152.Description: Decent pants that blend into the surroundings.
item_41152.Name: Camouflaged Decent Pants

item_41153.Description: This is a great camouflage job! The pants, well, they're not bad per se...
item_41153.Name: Camouflaged Nice Pants

item_41154.Description: Don't drop these in the forest or you'll never find them again.
item_41154.Name: Camouflaged Quality Pants

item_41155.Description: These look like really soft plants. Wait, those are soft pants. That's great camo.
item_41155.Name: Camouflaged Great Pants

item_41171.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew. The sinews were not properly cured and stink beyond comprehension.
item_41171.Name: Decent Snail Greaves

item_41172.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew. Only somewhat stinky.
item_41172.Name: Nice Snail Greaves

item_41173.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew.
item_41173.Name: Quality Snail Greaves

item_41176.Name: Astounding Snail Greaves

item_41177.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew.
item_41177.Name: Awesome Snail Greaves

item_41201.Description: Kind of revealing. But very comfortable.
item_41201.Name: Nice Spring Fairy Leggings

item_41202.Description: Kind of revealing. But very comfortable.
item_41202.Name: Quality Spring Fairy Leggings

item_41203.Description: Kind of revealing. But very comfortable.
item_41203.Name: Great Spring Fairy Leggings

item_41221.Description: Simple bits of metal designed to fit on the lower legs and haunches of a wolf.
item_41221.Name: Shoddy Werewolf Hindguard

item_41222.Description: Simple bits of metal designed to fit on the lower legs and haunches of a wolf.
item_41222.Name: Rough Werewolf Hindguard

item_41223.Description: Simple bits of metal designed to fit on the lower legs and haunches of a wolf.
item_41223.Name: Crude Werewolf Hindguard

item_41224.Description: Strong metal designed to fit on the lower legs and haunches of a wolf.
item_41224.Name: Decent Werewolf Hindguard

item_41225.Description: Strong metal designed to fit on the lower legs and haunches of a wolf.
item_41225.Name: Nice Werewolf Hindguard

item_41226.Description: Strong metal designed to fit on the lower legs and haunches of a wolf.
item_41226.Name: Quality Werewolf Hindguard

item_41227.Description: Strong metal designed to fit on the lower legs and haunches of a wolf.
item_41227.Name: Great Werewolf Hindguard

item_41228.Name: Amazing Werewolf Hindguard

item_41229.Name: Astounding Werewolf Hindguard

item_41230.Description: Strong metal designed to fit on the lower legs and haunches of a wolf.
item_41230.Name: Awesome Werewolf Hindguard

item_41301.Description: Worn leather pants with metal meticulously inserted into them. Whoever made these lacked skill in leatherworking, but made up for it with time and attention to detail.
item_41301.Name: Desert Vagabond Pants

item_41302.Description: This is the latest masterpiece of rakshasa leatherworking, designed to replace the old Ravana armor they can no longer create. In many ways, this surpasses anything from their homeworld, a testament to rakshasa skill... and the toughness of beasts in Alharth.
item_41302.Name: Rakshasian Elite Leggings

item_41303.Description: Thick matted hair combined with spider silk. These feel great. No, really. They don't look great, but they feel great.
item_41303.Name: Yeti Leggings

item_41304.Description: Nice greaves. Vaguely stylish yet vaguely protective.
item_41304.Name: Basic Pants

item_41305.Description: The isolated elf colony of Sedgewick Forest prefers armor of this type because it reminds them of their home in Verta. It's been explained to them that nobody in Verta dresses this way anymore, but they don't seem to care.
item_41305.Name: Thentree Skirt

item_41306.Description: A protective garment that also keeps you light on your feet. The goblin smell, unfortunately, doesn't wash out.
item_41306.Name: Goblin Kilt

item_41307.Description: Used by the typical troops of the Crone Hegemony.
item_41307.Name: Peltast Kilt

item_41308.Description: Not really that comfortable unless you're in a blizzard, but then they are really cozy.
item_41308.Name: Insulated Pants

item_41309.Description: It's amazing that these awkwardly-riveted pieces of scorpion and beetle carapace give you any mobility at all. But they do! Just don't sit down too quickly, and you'll be fine.
EffectDescs: You reflect 5% of any physical attack damage (Slashing, Piercing, or Crushing) back at the attacker.
item_41309.Name: Scorpiclaw Leggings

item_41310.Description: The terrifying Ankara lord wore these pants all the time. Like, nonstop. But they don't smell. Eerie.
EffectDescs: You reflect 5% of any physical attack damage (Slashing, Piercing, or Crushing) back at the attacker.
item_41310.Name: General Pask's Leggings

item_41311.Description: The stitching on these leather pants is awful. And the quality of the leather sub-par. But goblins forced to buy their own armor often choose these for cost reasons.
item_41311.Name: Cheap Goblin Leggings

item_42002.Description: Pretty shoddy workmanship... but hey, it's armor.
item_42002.Name: Basic Breastplate

item_42003.Description: This is the grossest possible thing. But all the blood smears make it harder for monsters to tell where to stab you.
item_42003.Name: Comfortable Ancient Shirt

item_42005.Description: This simple platemail has sufficient protection, but it could do with more padding. Very uncomfortable!
item_42005.Name: Sturdy Shirt

item_42006.Description: Strong enough for a Human, but made for a Goblin. By slaves who toil in very poor working conditions.
item_42006.Name: Goblin Breastplate

item_42007.Description: This is good armor, but rather uncomfortable if you have chest hair... lots of pinching.
item_42007.Name: Goblin Chain Shirt

item_42009.Description: Strong armor with a strong statement to make: "I like red!"
item_42009.Name: Quality Breastplate

item_42010.Description: The breastplate features a perfectly preserved Giant Snail shell.
item_42010.Name: Snail Plate Armor

item_42011.Description: Sacrificing armor for killing power, these robes are popular with wizards. A Necromancy Gem is woven into the chest.
item_42011.Name: Robes of Malediction

item_42012.Description: Imbued with potent magic, the ever-patching shirt is constantly fixing itself.
item_42012.Name: Everpatching Shirt

item_42013.Description: The best armor ever! Oh, except it rusts easily, squeaks a lot, is hot in the summer and cold in the winter, very uncomfortable, and particularly prone to lightning damage. And also it's not the best armor in terms of armor capacity. But ... but it's not bad.
item_42013.Name: Knight's Armor

item_42014.Description: It was in the bedding of Old Fangsworth's lair.
item_42014.Name: Tiger-Urine-Encrusted Shirt

item_42015.Description: Lawara the amnesiac was wearing this when she first awoke. It clearly used to be something special, but now it's barely holding together.
item_42015.Name: Lawara's Mangled Platemail

item_42017.Description: Another piece of once-ceremonial armor that was retrofitted for combat during the Elf-Dwarf wars. The suit has since become a favorite of elven warriors thanks to its handy odor-repulsion magic. And also, of course, its insane amount of protection.
item_42017.Name: Elven Ceremonial Suit

item_42023.Description: Woven with fairy magic, this lovely shirt regenerates its leaves continuously. Unfortunately it is extremely itchy to wear. But noone said safety and comfort had to go hand in hand, so stop complaining.
item_42023.Name: Leafy Shirt

item_42027.Description: This gross shirt smells of urine. It provides no armor protection, and it's also very itchy.
item_42027.Name: Crude Undershirt

item_42028.Description: This simple platemail has sufficient protection, but it could do with more padding. Very uncomfortable!
item_42028.Name: Sturdy Shirt

item_42029.Description: Simple in design, but heavy on the armor plating.
item_42029.Name: Extra-Sturdy Shirt

item_42030.Description: Rust damage has taken a heavy toll on this breastplate. It's still functional, but you'll probably get rust stains all over yourself.
item_42030.Name: Corroded Breastplate

item_42031.Description: Somehow this breastplate got stuck onto a spider via sticky web! What are the odds? Unfortunately, spider acid has filled it with holes, but what a great story!
item_42031.Name: Spider-Worn Coat

item_42032.Description: This breastplate is very old, and a sequence of enchantments has been laid atop it to protect it from the elements.
item_42032.Name: Hunter's Breastplate

item_42033.Description: It's cotton! Breathable, pleasant, cotton. Yep. Cotton.
item_42033.Name: Cotton Undershirt

item_42034.Description: Inlaid with beautiful silver filigree, this cozy shirt looks gorgeous.
item_42034.Name: Silver-Threaded Shirt

item_42035.Description: This tough leather armor is interwoven with magical threads that supposedly keep psionic attacks at bay.
item_42035.Name: Orcish Coat

item_42036.Description: When you don this strange metal suit, you can feel your sense of empathy and community diminish. All the better to kill without remorse!
item_42036.Name: Coat of the Winter Court

item_42037.Description: When the dwarves were holed up under Serbule so many centuries ago, they didn't have a lot to do but make really resilient armor. The resiliency magic bleeds over to the wearer.
item_42037.Name: Dwarven Soldier Breastplate

item_42038.Description: Makeshift Summer armor. It grants empathy to the wearer, though only those who are attuned to such things will notice.
item_42038.Name: Coat of the Summer Court

item_42039.Description: Designed by a spiteful necromancer bent on conquering a city, these robes seethe with hatred. And it turns out that pure hatred is pretty warm, providing mild protection against the cold.
item_42039.Name: Robes of Hateful Comeuppance

item_42040.Description: When thousands of Rakshasa warriors arrived on Alharth, they wore suits of armor like this, designed to accommodate all environments. The secret to their crafting is lost to the Rakshasa living here now.
item_42040.Name: Ravana Soldier Coat

item_42041.Description: The rings of this chain suit are ridiculously thick, resulting in a very protective garment that is pretty ugly -- and very conductive of cold and electricity.
item_42041.Name: Thickened Chainmail Shirt

item_42042.Description: Pretty shoddy workmanship... but hey, it's armor.
item_42042.Name: Basic Breastplate

item_42043.Description: This simple platemail has sufficient protection, but it could do with more padding. Very uncomfortable!
item_42043.Name: Sturdy Shirt

item_42044.Description: Strong armor with a strong statement to make: "I like red!"
item_42044.Name: Quality Breastplate

item_42045.Description: Itchy and viney, but the magic is impressively resilient.
item_42045.Name: Spring Fairy Top

item_42046.Description: This thick and ungainly thing was the preferred armor of the ancient Dwarven Stalwarts. It's easy to see why: this armor is very... stalwart.
item_42046.Name: Stalwart Breastplate

item_42047.Description: A strange mechanism that can augment an arthropod's venomous attack capabilities. (Only wearable by spiders.)
item_42047.Name: Harness of Poisons

item_42048.Description: Cozy and warm, with lots of fur trim.
item_42048.Name: Syndra's Winter Coat

item_42049.Description: Worn leather with metal meticulously inserted into it. Whoever made this lacked skill in leatherworking, but made up for it with time and attention to detail.
item_42049.Name: Desert Vagabond Shirt

item_42050.Description: This is the latest masterpiece of rakshasa leatherworking, designed to replace the old Ravana armor they can no longer create. In many ways, this surpasses anything from their homeworld, a testament to rakshasa skill... and the toughness of beasts in Alharth.
item_42050.Name: Rakshasian Elite Coat

item_42051.Description: Thick matted hair combined with spider silk. It's kind of sticky, making it a little too form-fitting. It's surprisingly durable, though!
item_42051.Name: Yeti Jacket

item_42052.Description: Pretty shoddy workmanship... but hey, it's armor.
item_42052.Name: Basic Breastplate

item_42053.Description: The isolated elf colony of Sedgewick Forest prefers armor of this type because it reminds them of their home in Verta. It's been explained to them that nobody in Verta dresses this way anymore, but they don't seem to care.
item_42053.Name: Thentree Harness

item_42054.Description: When you don this strange metal suit, you can feel your sense of empathy and community diminish. All the better to kill without remorse!
item_42054.Name: Great Coat of the Winter Court

item_42055.Description: Used by the typical troops of the Crone Hegemony.
item_42055.Name: Peltast Coat

item_42056.Description: It's gotten a bit frayed from use, but it's still thick and warm.
item_42056.Name: Insulated Coat

item_42057.Description: Made of giant beetle and scorpion carapace, this stfling, awkward, and heavy coat rewards those who have the fortitude to endure wearing it.
EffectDescs: You reflect 5% of any physical attack damage (Slashing, Piercing, or Crushing) back at the attacker.
item_42057.Name: Scorpiclaw Suit

item_42058.Description: The general seems to have customized this Scorpiclaw suit to his own strange needs: there's a hidden compartment inside.
EffectDescs: You reflect 5% of any physical attack damage (Slashing, Piercing, or Crushing) back at the attacker.
item_42058.Name: General Pask's Armor

item_42059.Description: The preferred armor of goblin tribes on serious budget crunches.
item_42059.Name: Cheap Goblin Chain Shirt

item_42101.Description: Poor-quality leather has been crudely woven into a fairly repulsive shirt. It's essentially made of garbage.
item_42101.Name: Shoddy Leather Shirt

item_42102.Description: A novice-quality piece of work, with embarrassingly wide stitches.
item_42102.Name: Rough Leather Shirt

item_42103.Description: Not nice to look at, but its got it where it counts. Which is to say the chest region.
item_42103.Name: Crude Leather Shirt

item_42105.Description: This is a pro-quality piece of equipment! The stitching isn't even visible from the outside. Fancy.
item_42105.Name: Nice Leather Shirt

item_42106.Description: This looks great! Very professional. And moderately comfortable, too!
item_42106.Name: Quality Leather Shirt

item_42107.Description: A soft leather vest with thick reinforced sleeves. Who knew wearing ten pounds of leather could be this not-horrible?
item_42107.Name: Great Leather Shirt

item_42108.Description: This leather armor is so comfortable, it's almost criminal.
item_42108.Name: Amazing Leather Shirt

item_42109.Description: This is a masterpiece. It's got little hidden straps and buckles to make sure you can fit it perfectly to any form.
item_42109.Name: Astounding Leather Shirt

item_42110.Description: Wow! Awesome! You could sleep in this baby, it's so comfortable.
item_42110.Name: Awesome Leather Shirt

item_42144.Description: Extra insulated to protect against winds.
item_42144.Name: Decent Winter Coat

item_42145.Description: Cozy and warm, with lots of fur trim.
item_42145.Name: Nice Winter Coat

item_42146.Description: A professional-looking winter coat with heavy insulation.
item_42146.Name: Quality Winter Coat

item_42147.Description: When winter comes and you need a great coat, now you have one. During summer, though, this is a "nice" coat. At best.
item_42147.Name: Great Winter Coat

item_42163.Description: This crumpled leather shirt can't decide whether it wants to be nimble or protective, instead failing at both.
item_42163.Name: Crude Evasion Shirt

item_42164.Description: This is incredibly light leather chest armor. You can really move around in this baby. Pity about the stitching. And the color. And the design.
item_42164.Name: Decent Evasion Shirt

item_42165.Description: You feel nice wearing a leather shirt like this. Nice enough to be able to dodge arrows.
item_42165.Name: Nice Evasion Shirt

item_42166.Description: A pro made this leather armor, and aside from some unusual choices in tailoring, there's not much to complain about.
item_42166.Name: Quality Evasion Shirt

item_42201.Description: It sucks. But it makes you look less intimidating. Which might be a good thing or a bad thing.
item_42201.Name: Shoddy Cloth Shirt

item_42202.Description: A few years ago, the humans of Statehelm decided shirts like this were ironically in fashion. That time has come and gone, however, and now it's just hideous again.
item_42202.Name: Rough Cloth Shirt

item_42203.Description: Hm... there must be something nice to say about this shirt. Ah! The pockets are sewn on straight. Nice!
item_42203.Name: Crude Cloth Shirt

item_42204.Description: Good for lounging around the house. Where nobody will see you.
item_42204.Name: Decent Cloth Shirt

item_42205.Description: Not exactly formalwear, but not humiliating either.
item_42205.Name: Nice Cloth Shirt

item_42206.Description: Pretty high quality. Good thread count, decent coloration, not too tight. Good stuff.
item_42206.Name: Quality Cloth Shirt

item_42207.Description: Simultaneously elegant and protective. If you own only one shirt, ... then you probably can't afford this one.
item_42207.Name: Great Cloth Shirt

item_42253.Description: A poor piece of Clothing,  but it does at least blend into the surroundings well.
item_42253.Name: Camouflaged Crude Shirt

item_42254.Description: People won't realize how silly your shirt is, because they won't even notice you're there! Much.
item_42254.Name: Camouflaged Decent Shirt

item_42255.Description: Is it a camouflaged nice shirt, or a nice camouflaged shirt? A little of both, probably.
item_42255.Name: Camouflaged Nice Shirt

item_42256.Description: It's hard to see, which is good for a camouflaged shirt.
item_42256.Name: Camouflaged Quality Shirt

item_42257.Description: This is the sort of shirt a masterful guerilla elf might wear. Not that you'd ever see them wearing it, of course, but that's the point.
item_42257.Name: Camouflaged Great Shirt

item_42271.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew. The sinews were not properly cured and stink beyond comprehension.
item_42271.Name: Decent Snail Coat

item_42272.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew. Only somewhat stinky.
item_42272.Name: Nice Snail Coat

item_42359.Name: Astounding Werewolf Barding

item_42371.Description: Pieces of chitin and scraps of metal are held together with thick webbing. This would fit on a spider.
item_42371.Name: Shoddy Spider Casing

item_42372.Description: Pieces of chitin and scraps of metal are held together with thick webbing. This should make a spider somewhat tougher.
item_42372.Name: Rough Spider Casing

item_42373.Description: Pieces of chitin and metal are sewn into reinforced webbing to create a suit for spiders.
item_42373.Name: Crude Spider Casing

item_42374.Description: Pieces of chitin and metal are sewn into reinforced webbing to create a suit for spiders.
item_42374.Name: Decent Spider Casing

item_42375.Description: Pieces of chitin and strong metal are sewn into reinforced webbing to create a powerful armor suit for spiders.
item_42375.Name: Nice Spider Casing

item_42376.Description: Pieces of chitin and strong metal are sewn into reinforced webbing to create a powerful armor suit for spiders.
item_42376.Name: Quality Spider Casing
