item_43001.Description: These are so slimy, wearing them is like sticking dozens of leeches to your hands.
item_43001.Name: Moldy Ancient Gloves

item_43002.Description: Wow, off-red utility gloves. Nice. I guess.
item_43002.Name: Basic Gloves

item_43003.Description: The padding is worn through in all the right places, making it easy to fight in these disgusting gloves.
item_43003.Name: Comfortable Ancient Gloves

item_43007.Description: Who doesn't love steel plate armor on your hands? Well... besides wizards?
item_43007.Name: Slightly Rusty Gauntlets

item_43008.Description: Protects your hands so well that you can even punch harder than before.
item_43008.Name: Goblin Fist Wraps

item_43009.Description: They're vaguely gold-colored, because gold is the color of quality.
item_43009.Name: Quality Gloves

item_43012.Description: Great for punching! Also, somehow makes your kicks hurt more, too... weird.
item_43012.Name: Spiked Gloves

item_43013.Description: Popular among the guards of the Council, these gloves are lined with lead to protect against mind control. Of course, the lead would be more effective if it was on your head instead of your hands, but nobody really wants a bunch of lead on their head.
item_43013.Name: Republic Gloves

item_43014.Description: Thick smelly gloves that have been through a few fights
item_43014.Name: Goblin Gloves

item_43015.Description: Light, delicate gloves that seem far more fragile than they really are.
item_43015.Name: Fey Gloves

item_43016.Description: Dainty gloves made of a stretchy material. They could fit any sized hands, but were made for a child.
item_43016.Name: Ursula's Gloves

item_43017.Description: Insulated gloves for the most demanding of environments.
item_43017.Name: Temperature Control Gloves

item_43018.Description: Well, there's no name inscribed on them or anything. But you could give them a name if you wanted!
item_43018.Name: Nameless Gauntlets

item_43021.Description: Instead of wearing these, why not just strap some dead animals to your hands? That would be more stylish, more convenient, and less smelly.
item_43021.Name: Shoddy Leather Gloves

item_43022.Description: Although clearly intended to be gloves, these are little more than wads of leather in vaguely-hand-shaped form. Expect immense amounts of palm sweat!
item_43022.Name: Rough Leather Gloves

item_43023.Description: The craftsmanship of these gloves is adequate, but the material is poor, resulting in a functional pair of gloves that aren't much fun to wear.
item_43023.Name: Crude Leather Gloves

item_43024.Description: These still get insanely hot and sweaty when worn, but at least they're kind of fashionable. Kind of.
item_43024.Name: Decent Leather Gloves

item_43025.Description: Made of reasonable materials, these gloves are nice. Just nice.
item_43025.Name: Nice Leather Gloves

item_43026.Description: These gloves were made by someone with a keen sense of anatomy, allowing a full range of motion.
item_43026.Name: Quality Leather Gloves

item_43027.Description: Pleasant to wear and reasonably protective.
item_43027.Name: Great Leather Gloves

item_43028.Description: These soft elegant gloves have custom gripping surfaces to make sure you never slip up in combat.
item_43028.Name: Amazing Leather Gloves

item_43029.Description: These gloves are so light, yet so protective! Astonishing craftsmanship.
item_43029.Name: Astounding Leather Gloves

item_43030.Description: They're as comfortable as not wearing any gloves, and as protective as wearing plate metal on your hands.
item_43030.Name: Awesome Leather Gloves

item_43031.Description: Designed for orcish scouts and mobile assault troops, these gloves are patterned after the famous orcish plate gauntlets, but just made out of many layers of leather. Nobody really loves the result, but it's still better than steel gauntlets if you're trying to aim a bow.
item_43031.Name: Orcish Gloves

item_43032.Description: These freezing-cold gloves are hard to don, but once worn, they reveal themselves to be remarkably dextrous.
item_43032.Name: Gauntlets of the Winter Court

item_43033.Description: Oversized gloves were the style hundreds of years ago, which is why these dwarven gauntlets can fit your hands.
item_43033.Name: Dwarven Soldier Gauntlets

item_43034.Description: Oddly warm to the touch, even in cold weather, these makeshift Summer Court gloves protect from frostbite.
item_43034.Name: Gauntlets of the Summer Court

item_43035.Description: These super-thick chainmail gloves are used by orcish arena fighters. They're uncomfortable and ugly, but very thick.
item_43035.Name: Orcish Gladiator Gloves

item_43036.Description: Wow, off-red utility gloves. Nice. I guess.
item_43036.Name: Basic Gloves

item_43038.Description: They're vaguely gold-colored, because gold is the color of quality.
item_43038.Name: Quality Gloves

item_43039.Description: Magic gauntlets that were in a giant spider's hoard for decades, taking some of the spider's aspect.
item_43039.Name: Venom Piercers

item_43040.Description: The Dwarven Stalwarts were hammer-lovers to a fault, and these thick gauntlets were engineered with hammers in mind.
item_43040.Name: Stalwart Gauntlets

item_43041.Description: The isolated elf colony of Sedgewick Forest prefers armor of this type because it reminds them of their home in Verta. It's been explained to them that nobody in Verta dresses this way anymore, but they don't seem to care.
item_43041.Name: Thentree Gloves

item_43042.Description: These freezing-cold gloves are hard to don, but once worn, they reveal themselves to be remarkably dextrous.
item_43042.Name: Great Gauntlets of the Winter Court

item_43043.Description: Insulated gloves for the most demanding of environments.
item_43043.Name: Temperature Control Gloves

item_43044.Description: Used by the typical troops of the Crone Hegemony.
item_43044.Name: Peltast Gauntlets

item_43045.Description: Thick smelly gloves that have been through a few fights
item_43045.Name: Goblin Gloves

item_43056.Description: When goblin tribes suffer from high turnover and budget shortfalls, they often have to make do with armor like this.
item_43056.Name: Cheap Goblin Gloves

item_43101.Description: Warm and cozy without getting in the way of violence.
item_43101.Name: Ukorga's Furry Fistwraps

item_43102.Description: An attempt at perfect harmony: metal outside, wool inside. Unfortunately, the gloves get really sweaty and are prone to fungal infestation. Ew.
item_43102.Name: Ruggedized Gloves

item_43103.Description: The goblin-trained bear Graz was outfitted with these after he killed one too many overzealous goblin mages. (Only animals can wear these.)
item_43103.Name: Graz's Shackles

item_43104.Description: The legacy is one of rusting quietly in a cave for hundreds of years.
item_43104.Name: Legacy Gloves

item_43105.Description: Decades of spiderwebs have made the joints hard to open and close. It's hard to make magical gestures while wearing them, but on the bright side, they're silky smooth inside.
item_43105.Name: Webbed-Up Gloves

item_43106.Description: Lost in a cave and worn by generations of insane werewolves, these well-made gauntlets have become infused with lycanthropic power.
item_43106.Name: Claws of the Undone Beast

item_43108.Description: These were once used in ceremonies, not combat, but they turned out to work pretty well there too, as long as you're not trying to do anything too terribly dextrous.
item_43108.Name: Elven Gauntlets

item_43109.Description: Designed by a spiteful necromancer bent on conquering a city, these cloth gloves seethe with hatred. And it turns out that pure hatred is pretty warm, providing mild protection against the cold.
item_43109.Name: Gloves of Hateful Comeuppance

item_43110.Description: When thousands of Rakshasa warriors arrived on Alharth, they wore suits of armor like this, designed to accommodate all environments. The secret to their crafting is lost to the Rakshasa living here now.
item_43110.Name: Ravana Soldier Gloves

item_43111.Description: Thick smelly gloves that the goblin Jumjab augmented. A Necromancy gem has been embedded into the right palm.
item_43111.Name: Jumjab's Necrogloves

item_43112.Description: Worn leather with metal meticulously inserted into it. Whoever made this lacked skill in leatherworking, but made up for it with time and attention to detail.
item_43112.Name: Desert Vagabond Gloves

item_43113.Description: This is the latest masterpiece of rakshasa leatherworking, designed to replace the old Ravana armor they can no longer create. In many ways, this surpasses anything from their homeworld, a testament to rakshasa skill... and the toughness of beasts in Alharth.
item_43113.Name: Rakshasian Elite Gloves

item_43115.Description: Thick matted hair combined with spider silk. These feel great. No, really. They don't look great, but they feel great.
item_43115.Name: Yeti Gloves

item_43116.Description: Wow, off-red utility gloves. Nice. I guess.
item_43116.Name: Basic Gloves

item_43117.Description: Warmth is the key goal here. They're a little clumsy, but not enough to complain about.
item_43117.Name: Insulated Gloves

item_43118.Description: Made of immaculately-carved pieces of giant insect carapace, these are a work of mechanical art. Heavy and prone to painful pinching, they are tolerable only to hardened warriors.
EffectDescs: You reflect 4% of any physical attack damage (Slashing, Piercing, or Crushing) back at the attacker.
item_43118.Name: Scorpiclaw Gauntlets

item_43119.Description: These scorpiclaw gauntlets were personally adjusted by the revered general. They are denser and yet more agile than one would expect.
EffectDescs: You reflect 4% of any physical attack damage (Slashing, Piercing, or Crushing) back at the attacker.
item_43119.Name: General Pask's Gloves

item_43121.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew. The sinews were not properly cured and stink beyond comprehension.
item_43121.Name: Decent Snail Gauntlets

item_43122.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew. Only somewhat stinky.
item_43122.Name: Nice Snail Gauntlets

item_43123.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew.
item_43123.Name: Quality Snail Gauntlets

item_43124.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew.
item_43124.Name: Great Snail Gauntlets

item_43125.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew.
item_43125.Name: Amazing Snail Gauntlets

item_43126.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew.
item_43126.Name: Astounding Snail Gauntlets

item_43127.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew.
item_43127.Name: Awesome Snail Gauntlets

item_43141.Description: Simple bits of metal designed to fit on the front legs and claws of a wolf.
item_43141.Name: Shoddy Werewolf Foreguards

item_43142.Description: Simple bits of metal designed to fit on the front legs and claws of a wolf.
item_43142.Name: Rough Werewolf Foreguards

item_43143.Description: Simple bits of metal designed to fit on the front legs and claws of a wolf.
item_43143.Name: Crude Werewolf Foreguards

item_43144.Description: Strong metal designed to fit on the front legs and claws of a wolf.
item_43144.Name: Decent Werewolf Foreguards

item_43145.Description: Strong metal designed to fit on the front legs and claws of a wolf.
item_43145.Name: Nice Werewolf Foreguards

item_43146.Description: Strong metal designed to fit on the front legs and claws of a wolf.
item_43146.Name: Quality Werewolf Foreguards

item_43147.Description: Strong metal designed to fit on the front legs and claws of a wolf.
item_43147.Name: Great Werewolf Foreguards

item_43148.Description: Strong metal designed to fit on the front legs and claws of a wolf.
item_43148.Name: Amazing Werewolf Foreguards

item_43149.Description: Strong metal designed to fit on the front legs and claws of a wolf.
item_43149.Name: Astounding Werewolf Foreguards

item_43150.Description: Strong metal designed to fit on the front legs and claws of a wolf.
item_43150.Name: Awesome Werewolf Foreguards

item_44003.Description: A thick layer of mold lines the inside, helping to seal the helmet to your head.
item_44003.Name: Comfortable Ancient Helm

item_44006.Description: It smells like spores and dysentery, but it seems to have interesting mushroom powers.
item_44006.Name: Whitecap

item_44008.Description: The finest in slave-made head protection.
item_44008.Name: Goblin Helmet

item_44011.Description: Named by a bard who was having a bad day, this jaunty hat is actually pretty despair-free.
item_44011.Name: Jaunty Hat of Despair

item_44012.Description: Knights love this sort of thing. Hope they don't go out in a thunderstorm though...
item_44012.Name: Knight's Helm

item_44014.Description: A fairly basic helmet with some unnecessary stylistic flourishes.
item_44014.Name: Flanged Helm

item_44015.Description: Truth in advertising: this is not a pretty helmet. It has other charms, though, such as a deep-seated aroma of spoiled cheese.
item_44015.Name: Ugly Helm

item_44016.Description: This hat was stuck to a spider for years. There's so much webbing that you can't get all of it off, and it'll keep falling in your face while you try to murder things.
item_44016.Name: Web-Coated Hat

item_44017.Description: A cotton hat that's good in the cold.
item_44017.Name: Cotton Balaclava

item_44018.Description: A horrific cotton cap. High quality in every way, but just... ugly.
item_44018.Name: Thimble Pete's Awful Cap

item_44019.Description: For orcs that rely on speed and stealth to survive, this leather helmet is the standard. It's not really the best possible cap, but standards usually aren't.
item_44019.Name: Orcish Cap

item_44020.Description: Ceremonial armor refitted for battlefield use, this helm looks sharp -- and can make the wearer look sharp, too, provided they know how to wear it with style.
item_44020.Name: Elven Officer's Helm

item_44021.Description: While vaguely protective, this lopsided helmet is so unbalancing that you're almost better off just going into combat without a helm at all.
item_44021.Name: Shoddy Leather Helmet

item_44022.Description: Designed to protect from concussions and minor scrapes, this helmet has the serious drawbacks of reduced visibility, unpleasant odor, and terrible craftsmanship.
item_44022.Name: Rough Leather Helmet

item_44023.Description: While the craftsmanship is adequate, the materials are not, and this helmet looks more like a dead beaver than a helm.
item_44023.Name: Crude Leather Helmet

item_44024.Description: A well-made helmet that will keep you alive in combat. But you'll sweat profusely in it, and you don't want to know what it's going to do to your hair.
item_44024.Name: Decent Leather Helmet

item_44025.Description: A comfy helmet that is almost (but not quite) attractive, too!
item_44025.Name: Nice Leather Helmet

item_44026.Description: Good materials and great craftsmanship combine in a helmet that breathes easy and protects from nearly any injury.
item_44026.Name: Quality Leather Helmet

item_44027.Description: A helmet that's stylish and also functional! Great.
item_44027.Name: Great Leather Helmet

item_44028.Description: This helmet goes beyond mere adequacy. It says "adequate isn't enough!" It takes it one step farther, all the way to more-than-adequate.
item_44028.Name: Amazing Leather Helmet

item_44029.Description: A hat you wouldn't be embarrassed being seen in, and so light and protective! Anti-odor components keep it smelling fresh all day, too.
item_44029.Name: Astounding Leather Helmet

item_44030.Description: A great helmet with great safety features, like extra padding to keep sweat out of your eyes and customized ear-holes to make sure you never miss a thing.
item_44030.Name: Awesome Leather Helmet

item_44201.Description: This bizarre helmet affects the mind of the wearer ever so slightly. Just a touch.
item_44201.Name: Helm of the Winter Court

item_44202.Description: "Coif of Calamities" is inscribed inside, in tiny lettering. It doesn't seem very calamitous, though. Maybe it was some sort of ancient marketing campaign.
item_44202.Name: Coif of Calamities

item_44203.Description: The damaged remains of an intellect-enhancement helmet.
item_44203.Name: Intellect Augmentation Helmet

item_44204.Description: A resilient piece of history! Perfect for the dwarf fetishist in your life. Or you could wear it in battle, if that's what you're into.
item_44204.Name: Dwarven Soldier Helm

item_44205.Description: This was once a Winter Court helm that was repurposed. Instead of twisting the mind, it protects against such things.
item_44205.Name: Helm of the Summer Court

item_44206.Description: Designed by a spiteful necromancer bent on conquering a city, this hood seethes with hatred. And it turns out that pure hatred is pretty warm, providing mild protection against the cold.
item_44206.Name: Hood of Hateful Comeuppance

item_44207.Description: Fae blacksmiths have infused the metal of this helm with the essence of eternity, meaning that this helm has never not existed. Don't think about it too much.
item_44207.Name: Indestructible Fae Knight's Helm

item_44208.Description: When thousands of Rakshasa warriors arrived on Alharth, they wore suits of armor like this, designed to accommodate all environments. The secret to their crafting is lost to the Rakshasa living here now.
item_44208.Name: Ravana Soldier Helm

item_44209.Description: This ugly leather thing is supposed to be worn on the head, apparently.
item_44209.Name: Orcish Gladiator Cap

item_44214.Description: The face of a big snail has been made into a makeshift helmet.
item_44214.Name: Snail Mother's Face

item_44215.Description: It's a tough helmet that was once used by the elite Dwarven Stalwarts. But that was a thousand years ago, and more recent wearers have not been big on armor maintenance. It's still a great helm, but you imagine it was once even more impressive.
item_44215.Name: Stalwart Helmet

item_44216.Description: Worn leather with metal meticulously inserted into it. Whoever made this lacked skill in leatherworking, but made up for it with time and attention to detail.
item_44216.Name: Desert Vagabond Cap

item_44217.Description: This is the latest masterpiece of rakshasa leatherworking, designed to replace the old Ravana armor they can no longer create. In many ways, this surpasses anything from their homeworld, a testament to rakshasa skill... and the toughness of beasts in Alharth.
item_44217.Name: Rakshasian Elite Helm

item_44218.Description: Thick matted hair combined with spider silk. The silk gets all in your hair and eyes and is rather uncomfortable, but it's really warm.
item_44218.Name: Yeti Mask

item_44220.Description: The isolated elf colony of Sedgewick Forest prefers armor of this type because it reminds them of their home in Verta. It's been explained to them that nobody in Verta dresses this way anymore, but they don't seem to care.
item_44220.Name: Thentree Helmet

item_44221.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew. The sinews were not properly cured and stink beyond comprehension.
item_44221.Name: Decent Snail Helm

item_44222.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew. Only somewhat stinky.
item_44222.Name: Nice Snail Helm

item_44223.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew.
item_44223.Name: Quality Snail Helm

item_44224.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew.
item_44224.Name: Great Snail Helm

item_44225.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew.
item_44225.Name: Amazing Snail Helm

item_44226.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew.
item_44226.Name: Astounding Snail Helm

item_44227.Description: Made of snail shells and sinew.
item_44227.Name: Awesome Snail Helm

item_44241.Description: Hammered together from simple materials, for a simple battle cow.
item_44241.Name: Decent Cow Champron

item_44242.Description: A better-made helmet for a better-made bovine.
item_44242.Name: Nice Cow Champron

item_44243.Description: Hammered and polished and ready for battle.
item_44243.Name: Quality Cow Champron

item_44244.Description: Hammered and polished and ready for battle.
item_44244.Name: Great Cow Champron

item_44245.Description: Hammered and polished and ready for battle.
item_44245.Name: Amazing Cow Champron

item_44246.Description: Hammered and polished and ready for battle.
item_44246.Name: Astounding Cow Champron

item_44247.Description: Hammered and polished and ready for battle.
item_44247.Name: Awesome Cow Champron

item_44261.Description: It's metal. It fits on a werewolf. These are the only positive attributes.
item_44261.Name: Shoddy Werewolf Champron

item_44262.Description: It's metal. It fits on a werewolf. These are the only positive attributes.
item_44262.Name: Rough Werewolf Champron

item_44263.Description: It's metal. It fits on a werewolf. These are the only positive attributes.
item_44263.Name: Crude Werewolf Champron

item_44264.Description: A reasonable-looking metal helm for a werewolf.
item_44264.Name: Decent Werewolf Champron

item_44301.Description: This bizarre helmet affects the mind of the wearer ever so slightly. Just a touch.
item_44301.Name: Great Helm of the Winter Court

item_44302.Description: A blob of organic sentient tissue that you can kind of fit onto your head!
item_44302.Name: Lobe Hat

item_44303.Description: Used by the typical troops of the Crone Hegemony.
item_44303.Name: Peltast Hat

item_44304.Description: A garnet that floats around your head and emits light. This was obviously made by an apprentice still learning the craft. The enchantment is clumsy and the gem wobbles slightly in its orbit.
item_44304.Name: Orbiting Gem

item_44305.Description: Warm, warm, warm. A little smelly. But warm!
item_44305.Name: Insulated Hood

item_44306.Description: A freakish mask crafted by an unliving malevolence.
item_44306.Name: Empusa's Mask

item_44307.Description: A garnet that floats around your head and emits light. Not especially well-made, but it's still vaguely impressive.
item_44307.Name: Rohina's Mind Gem

item_44308.Description: This magic garnet can float around your head and emit light. It also emanates hard-won wisdom, and can whisper warnings and advice when you're about to do something stupid.
item_44308.Name: Monger's Boon

item_44309.Description: A terrifying visage made of hardened scorpion sinews backed by reflective beetle carapaces.
EffectDescs: You reflect 4% of any physical attack damage (Slashing, Piercing, or Crushing) back at the attacker.
item_44309.Name: Scorpiclaw Mask

item_44310.Description: The Ankara leader claimed to wear this mask even when resting, often saying that a true warrior could never be unprepared.
EffectDescs: You reflect 4% of any physical attack damage (Slashing, Piercing, or Crushing) back at the attacker.
item_44310.Name: General Pask's Helm

item_44311.Description: A subpar goblin helm, dented and worn.
item_44311.Name: Cheap Goblin Helmet

item_45001.Description: Well, you wouldn't want to eat off this shield, that's for sure. But why would you eat off a shield? Just strap it on your arm, weirdo.
item_45001.Name: Moldy Ancient Shield

item_45003.Description: This sucker's seen some good times and some bad times. But mostly bad times, from the shield's point of view.
item_45003.Name: Battle-Hardened Shield

item_45004.Description: If this shield is so lucky, why did Marna give it away? Still, it seems pretty sturdy.
item_45004.Name: Marna's Lucky Shield

item_45005.Description: It's wood with some thin metal plating over it. Pretty sturdy, and also lightweight.
item_45005.Name: Sturdy Shield

item_45006.Description: Etchings in the Goblin language roughly translate to "I Bash Really Well". It sounds better in the native tongue.
item_45006.Name: Goblin Shield

item_45007.Description: Etchings in the Goblin language roughly translate to "I Don't Care About Your Feelings". It sounds better in the native tongue.
item_45007.Name: Goblin Shield

item_45010.Description: "You'll look protected yet stylish with the latest quality shield from Helena's Quality Killsuits."
item_45010.Name: Quality Shield

item_45011.Description: Made from a perfectly preserved Giant Snail shell.
item_45011.Name: Snail Shield

item_45012.Description: This was once owned by a powerful shaman who protected cute woodland animals. A tiny bit of his soul resides in this shield. If you don't use it, you're throwing away his life's work!
item_45012.Name: Defender of the Frail

item_45013.Description: This antique shield once had an insignia, but it's been dented and scratched beyond recognition.
item_45013.Name: Nameless Guardian's Shield

item_45014.Description: "You'll look protected yet stylish with the latest quality shield from Helena's Quality Killsuits."
item_45014.Name: Quality Shield

item_45015.Description: A thick wooden shield, etched with magical runes.
item_45015.Name: Oaken Shield

item_45016.Description: Found stuck to a giant spider, this shield has been scarred and pitted with acid. It looks pretty badass, but it's not really very protective.
item_45016.Name: Acid-Pitted Shield

item_45017.Description: Obtained from a human named Tyler, this shield seems to have been well-maintained.
item_45017.Name: Tyler's Shield

item_45018.Description: It's somewhat melted around the edges, but still pretty sturdy.
item_45018.Name: Tyler's Second-Favorite Shield

item_45019.Description: A mass-produced shield for non-elite orcs.
item_45019.Name: Orcish Targe

item_45020.Description: Although nothing special by elven standards, other races would kill for the secrets of the protective runes etched into this shield.
item_45020.Name: Elven Shield

item_45021.Description: Robust, like dwarves. Flammable, like dwarves.
item_45021.Name: Dwarven Targe

item_45022.Description: Obtained from a human named Nelson Ballard. It's not in the best condition, but it has been powerfully enchanted.
item_45022.Name: Nelson Ballard's Shield

item_45024.Description: It's wood with some thin metal plating over it. Pretty sturdy, and also lightweight.
item_45024.Name: Sturdy Shield

item_45025.Description: This shield was stuck to a big droach for decades. It apparently absorbed some of the droach's protective power.
item_45025.Name: Old Crusty's Backside

item_45026.Description: The elite Stalwarts used this sort of shield. It's hard to find fault with the design, except that it's super heavy.
item_45026.Name: Stalwart Targe

item_45027.Description: This is a fake: Ravana soldiers did not wear shields when they arrived on Alharth. This shield is a masterpiece made in the style of their armor.
item_45027.Name: Ravana Soldier Shield

item_45028.Description: Not many yetis use shields, but they aren't terrible. This one is made of super-thick wood that's been reinforced with pounds of spider silk.
item_45028.Name: Yeti Shield

item_45030.Description: The elves of Sedgewick Forest use shields like this for some reason.
item_45030.Name: Thentree Shield

item_45031.Description: This special testing shield grants the wielder immense health.
item_45031.Name: Admin Shield

item_45032.Description: The stock shield used by countless grunts in the Crone Hegemony.
item_45032.Name: Peltast Shield

item_45033.Description: An attractive longshield. The symbols on the back say "Lead Without Fear" in elvish.
item_45033.Name: Leader's Shield

item_45034.Description: Etchings in the Goblin language roughly translate to "I Have My Rights And I Don't Care About Yours". It sounds better in the native tongue.
item_45034.Name: Cheap Goblin Shield

item_46001.Description: Well, it's still got a pointy end and a handle. It should work fine.
item_46001.Name: Moldy Ancient Sword

item_46002.Description: It's a sword! Looks pretty sharp.
item_46002.Name: Basic Sword

item_46003.Description: The hilt has been worn smooth with use, leaving indentations that make it easier for neophytes to know how to hold it properly.
item_46003.Name: Battle-Hardened Sword

item_46005.Description: This is a basic sword that Joeh custom-modded over the years. It has a unique hilt, "speed stripes" on the blade, and the pommel lights up in the dark.
item_46005.Name: Joeh's Old Sword

item_46006.Description: This sword is sharp. Really sharp. As sharp as you can probably get without imbuing it with magic.
item_46006.Name: Quality Sword

item_46007.Description: Forged by the most skilled goblin weaponsmiths in the tri-county area.
item_46007.Name: Goblinblade

item_46008.Description: Crafted by dwarven blacksmith (and inveterate tree-stabber) Goh Rastuk. It was going to be imbued with anti-nature magic, but Goh didn't get around to it. It's still a nice sword, though.
item_46008.Name: Naturebane

item_46010.Description: Stained with blood, ash, and lightning scars, this dark, evil sword is cold to the touch. Which is kind of creepy. But it's surprisingly well-maintained, and wonderfully sharp! A necromancy gem is embedded in the hilt.
item_46010.Name: Blackened Sword

item_46011.Description: An old style of blade, favored by some werewolves but not many others.
item_46011.Name: Wolfbite

item_46012.Description: Silver is a poor metal for making weapons, and this pocked and marred blade shows it. But its effect against lycanthropes is quite pronounced.
EffectDescs: Deals +20 damage to lycanthropes,Dispels lycanthropic regeneration effects
item_46012.Name: Simple Silver Knife

item_46013.Description: An iron sword with a thick coat of silver on top.
EffectDescs: Deals +20 damage to lycanthropes,Dispels lycanthropic regeneration effects
item_46013.Name: Silvered Sword

item_46014.Description: Each orc is given a xiphos upon their attainment of adulthood. Made of cold iron, it has a broad blade that slightly favors strength over finesse.
item_46014.Name: Xiphos

item_46015.Description: It's a sword! Looks pretty sharp.
item_46015.Name: Basic Sword

item_46016.Description: This sword is sharp. Really sharp. As sharp as you can probably get without imbuing it with magic.
item_46016.Name: Quality Sword

item_46017.Description: This sword was stuck to a big spider. It's not really in good shape, but the holes in the blade make a neat whistling sound when you swing it.
item_46017.Name: Acid-Addled Blade

item_46018.Description: The  rune etchings in this blade were made by Elven masters. It is rare to find these so far from Elven homelands.
item_46018.Name: Elven Longsword

item_46019.Description: A very old style of Dwarven sword design.
item_46019.Name: Ancient Dwarven Blade

item_46020.Description: A blade that has been in the Sedgewick family line for generations.
item_46020.Name: Sedgewick's Honor

item_46022.Description: Goblin-made, with a focus on sharpness over all else.
item_46022.Name: Goblin Cutlass

item_46023.Description: Rust has taken its toll on this blade, but it's better than nothing.
item_46023.Name: Rusty Sword

item_46024.Description: It has an inscription: "Ensorcelled by Official Council Battlemages. Not for use by Rakshasa upon penalty of triple-death."
item_46024.Name: Council Trooper Sword

item_46025.Description: This is a really old weapon design! They don't make 'em like this anymore, for better or for worse.
item_46025.Name: Antique Spatha

item_46026.Description: This short sword is fairly terrible for anything except gutting livestock. But it does that really well!
EffectDescs: Melee attacks deal +5 damage to pigs
item_46026.Name: Pig Sticker

item_46027.Description: The hilt has been worn smooth with use, leaving indentations that make it easier for neophytes to know how to hold it properly.
item_46027.Name: Battle-Hardened Sword

item_46028.Description: This goblin-made weapon uses a manticore tail as a powerful injector. It's not a very good sword, but it's a great poisoning tool.
item_46028.Name: Gouging Stiletto

item_46029.Description: Stained with blood, ash, and lightning scars, this dark, evil sword is cold to the touch. Which is kind of creepy. But it's surprisingly well-maintained, and wonderfully sharp! A necromancy gem is embedded in the hilt.
item_46029.Name: Blackened Sword

item_46030.Description: An Elven Longsword that has been customized and modified by an expert. Dozens of little lines have been scratched into the blade, suggesting perhaps that the weapon has been used to kill a great many of something.
item_46030.Name: Janet Lew's Old Longsword

item_47001.Description: This staff has seen so much. Thankfully it can't talk.
item_47001.Name: Moldy Ancient Staff

item_47003.Description: It's charred and black from tossing hundreds of fireballs over the years, but it's still really comfortable to use.
item_47003.Name: Battle Hardened Staff

item_47004.Description: This was enchanted by a competent apprentice, but it's nothing special.
item_47004.Name: Sturdy Staff

item_47005.Description: An inscription in Elven reads "To my lovely Velkort, thanks for a great evening."
item_47005.Name: Velkort's Hand-Me-Down

item_47006.Description: This was made by an advanced apprentice, perhaps. While not a masterpiece, it avoids all the classic blunders of staff-making.
item_47006.Name: Quality Staff

item_47007.Description: Designed for inquisitive fire mages who like to explore new ways to burn things. What? No, it has nothing to do with inquisitions.
item_47007.Name: Inquisitor's Staff

item_47008.Description: Created in a bygone age by Jessandra the Cruel, who used it to save an orphanage from frost bees. Afterwards she declared that the staff had somehow tricked her into being kind and discarded it.
item_47008.Name: Fatestick

item_47009.Description: So named because it makes a sort of swishing noise. Nobody said weapons crafters were good at naming things.
item_47009.Name: Swishystick

item_47010.Description: Well-suited for staff-fighting, but a reasonable fire staff as well. Versatility!
item_47010.Name: Balanced Battlestaff

item_47011.Description: Hogan the staff-fighter's masterpiece... Well, a reasonable facsimile.
item_47011.Name: Hogan's Crippler

item_47012.Description: The lich Khyrulek crafted this wand during her centuries as a living corpse. It works better for the undead, but it's still pretty good for living people. (Not suitable for use as a fighting staff. This only works for fire magic.)
item_47012.Name: The Galvanizer

item_47013.Description: Handmade by a fairy, this staff is embarrassingly dainty.
item_47013.Name: Jesina's Staff

item_47015.Description: Very sturdy, but with a hollow core that gives it a strange heft when swung.
item_47015.Name: Goblin Staff

item_47016.Description: Made of burned bones, this staff is great for necromancers or fire mages. Less great for staff fighting, because burned bones aren't exactly quality building material. It's topped with a green necromancy gem.
item_47016.Name: Necromancer's Training Staff

item_47017.Description: A plain stick topped with a necromancy gem. Also works for Fire Magic and Staff Fighting.
item_47017.Name: Necromancy Test Staff

item_47018.Description: Elves create these staves when they're feeling old. The feeling usually passes after a few decades, though, and then the elves give them away.
item_47018.Name: Elven Staff

item_47019.Description: Honed to perfection by a staff expert who slowly went mad from Lycanthropy. It's a powerful weapon, though it is marred by long ugly claw marks.
item_47019.Name: Elerimon Staff

item_47020.Description: Infused with arcane protective rituals. While technically usable by fire Fire Mages and Staff Fighters, this weapon is designed to be wielded by those who fancy themselves healers.
item_47020.Name: Yagreet's Staff

item_47021.Description: Infused with arcane protective rituals. While technically usable by fire Fire Mages and Staff Fighters, this weapon is designed to be wielded by those who fancy themselves healers.
item_47021.Name: Yagreet's Staff

item_47022.Description: Given to neophyte druids to help them learn to hone their powers.
item_47022.Name: Druidic Training Stick

item_47023.Description: This was the favored match-stick of a minor flame spirit.
item_47023.Name: Bonfire Summoner

item_47024.Description: This was enchanted by a competent apprentice, but it's nothing special.
item_47024.Name: Sturdy Staff

item_47025.Description: This was made by an advanced apprentice, perhaps. While not a masterpiece, it avoids all the classic blunders of staff-making.
item_47025.Name: Quality Staff

item_47026.Description: Orloaka the goblin sage augmented this staff by filling its hollow core with tears collected from dying unicorns. Unicorns that he burned alive! (They were actually rhinos, not unicorns, though, so the enchantment isn't all that great.)
item_47026.Name: Orloaka's Staff

item_47027.Description: Used by Dwarves who must venture onto the battle field to aid fallen comrades.
item_47027.Name: Dwarven Medic Staff

item_47028.Description: This wooden staff is icy cold to the touch.
item_47028.Name: Freezing Staff

item_47029.Description: This seems to be made of enchanted ice. Kind of neat.
item_47029.Name: Staff of Ice

item_47030.Description: It doesn't have any sand magic or anything. It's just been in the sand a long time.
item_47030.Name: Sandy Staff

item_47031.Description: A staff with modest enchantments and modest grip and modest... well, let's just say the whole thing is 'modest'. In a 'not very good' kind of way.
item_47031.Name: Adequate Staff

item_47032.Description: A traditional druidic training staff has been augmented with dozens of arcane sigils and then dipped in ... something waxy. Probably something organic. Best not to contemplate.
item_47032.Name: Druidic Assault Staff

item_47033.Description: It's charred and black from tossing hundreds of fireballs over the years, but it's still really comfortable to use.
item_47033.Name: Battle Hardened Staff

item_47034.Description: It's charred and black from tossing hundreds of fireballs over the years, but it's still really comfortable to use.
item_47034.Name: Battle Hardened Staff

item_47035.Description: Inscribed with ancient rakshasa runes, this staff taps magic from another world. It's so hot that wielding it is a little bit painful.
item_47035.Name: Sun Warden

item_47036.Description: A customized staff with heavy weights on each end.
item_47036.Name: Roshun's Heavy Hitter

item_47101.Description: Come on, the bark isn't even fully removed from this stick! But it's pretty thick. (It will work for Staff Fighting but not Fire Magic abilities.)
item_47101.Name: Shoddy Melee Staff

item_47102.Description: Well, the bark has mostly been removed. Mostly. You'll only get a few splinters trying to use this. (It will work for Staff Fighting but not Fire Magic abilities.)
item_47102.Name: Rough Melee Staff

item_47103.Description: Look, someone figured out how to sand down the edges of a stick. Too bad the creator had no idea how to balance its weight. (It will work for Staff Fighting but not Fire Magic abilities.)
item_47103.Name: Crude Melee Staff

item_47104.Description: This staff is what you'd expect from a combat staff. Absolutely nothing special, though. This will work for Staff Fighting but lacks the runes necessary to work for Fire Magic.
item_47104.Name: Decent Melee Staff

item_47105.Description: Someone took a lot of time balancing and testing this staff to make sure it had the perfect weight distribution. This will work well for Staff Fighting, but lacks the runes necessary to work for Fire Magic.
item_47105.Name: Nice Melee Staff

item_47106.Description: Reinforced and quite sturdy. The weight distribution is slightly off because of the added metal, but it's hardly noticeable. This staff will work well for Staff Fighting, but lacks the runes necessary to work for Fire Magic.
item_47106.Name: Quality Melee Staff

item_47107.Description: The creator of this staff obviously had a lot of experience in making these. Largely metal-clad, but just the right amount of give from the wood. (This staff will work well for Staff Fighting, but lacks the runes necessary to work for Fire Magic.)
item_47107.Name: Great Melee Staff

item_47108.Description: This staff has a surprising amount of detail work. Grips at just the right places, metal tips, and a reduction of weight without adversely affecting durability. (It will work for Staff Fighting but not Fire Magic abilities.)
item_47108.Name: Amazing Melee Staff

item_47109.Description: This has all the relevant features that a staff fighter could want: durable, flexible, perfectly weighted, and makes a cool whistling sound when swung. (This will work for Staff Fighting but not Fire Magic abilities.)
item_47109.Name: Astounding Melee Staff

item_47110.Description: No words. Just swing this staff around a few times and you'll realize that its beauty surpasses the spoken language. (This will work for Staff Fighting but not Fire Magic abilities.)
item_47110.Name: Awesome Melee Staff

item_47121.Description: Come on, the bark isn't even fully removed from this stick! But it's pretty thick. Very basic Fire Magic runes have been crudely etched into the bark.
item_47121.Name: Shoddy Combat Staff

item_47122.Description: Well, the bark has mostly been removed. Mostly. You'll only get a few splinters trying to use this. The crude Fire Magic runes bear the mark of an amateur, but should work.
item_47122.Name: Rough Combat Staff

item_47123.Description: Look, someone figured out how to sand down the edges of a stick. Too bad the creator had no idea how to balance its weight. The Fire Magic runes look a little less haphazard, though.
item_47123.Name: Crude Combat Staff

item_47124.Description: This staff is what you'd expect from a combat staff. Absolutely nothing special, though. The standard Fire Magic runes have been etched into the wood.
item_47124.Name: Decent Combat Staff

item_47125.Description: Someone took a lot of time balancing and testing this staff to make sure it had the perfect weight distribution. Then Fire Magic runes were carefully sculpted into the wood.
item_47125.Name: Nice Combat Staff

item_47126.Description: Reinforced and quite sturdy. The weight distribution is slightly off because of the added metal, but it's hardly noticeable. The Fire Magic runes were burned through the metal, creating a neat tactile sensation.
item_47126.Name: Quality Combat Staff

item_47127.Description: The creator of this staff obviously had a lot of experience in making these. Largely metal-clad, but just the right amount of give from the wood. The Fire Magic Runes were burned in, and glow with comforting warmth when used.
item_47127.Name: Great Combat Staff

item_47128.Description: This staff has a surprising amount of detail work. Grips at just the right places, metal tips, and a reduction of weight without adversely affecting durability. The Fire Magic runes are elegant but understated.
item_47128.Name: Amazing Combat Staff

item_47129.Description: This has all the relevant features that a staff fighter or fire mage could want: durable, flexible, perfectly weighted, fire-spewing, and makes a cool whistling sound when swung.
item_47129.Name: Astounding Combat Staff

item_47130.Description: No words. Just swing this staff around a few times and you'll realize that its beauty surpasses the spoken language. The Fire Magic runes are a masterpiece of calligraphy, too.
item_47130.Name: Awesome Combat Staff

item_48004.Description: Shaped like a tiny pair of longswords.
item_48004.Name: Amulet of Competent Swording

item_48005.Description: A tiny metal fist on a chain.
item_48005.Name: Amulet of Unarmed Fighting

item_48006.Description: A tiny metal foot on a chain.
item_48006.Name: Amulet of Competent Unarmed Fighting

item_48007.Description: A figurine of a tiny metal fireball on a chain.
item_48007.Name: Amulet of Fire Magic

item_48008.Description: A figurine of two tiny metal fireballs on a chain.
item_48008.Name: Amulet of Competent Fire Magic

item_48010.Description: A figurine of a heart with many smaller little hearts attached to it. Eerie.
item_48010.Name: Amulet of Max Health +10

item_48011.Description: A figurine of two hearts combined. Weird.
item_48011.Name: Amulet of Max Health +15

item_48012.Description: A figurine of two hearts with little hearts coming off of them, as if they were in love. Creepy.
item_48012.Name: Amulet of Max Health +20

item_48037.Description: A figurine of a woman with hearts glued to every surface of her body. Very disturbing.
item_48037.Name: Amulet of Max Health +25

item_48045.Description: A figurine of a man holding a heart in his hands. The tiny heart pulses with its own rhythm.
item_48045.Name: Amulet of Max Health +30

item_48013.Description: A figurine of a tiny shield.
item_48013.Name: Amulet of Max Armor +5

item_48014.Description: A figurine of a tiny shield.
item_48014.Name: Amulet of Max Armor +10

item_48015.Description: A figurine of a tiny shield.
item_48015.Name: Amulet of Max Armor +15

item_48016.Description: A figurine of a tiny shield.
item_48016.Name: Amulet of Max Armor +20

item_48017.Description: A figurine of a tiny shield.
item_48017.Name: Amulet of Max Armor +25

item_48044.Description: A figurine of a tiny shield.
item_48044.Name: Amulet of Max Armor +30

item_48018.Description: A figurine of two wolves killing a deer together. So tiny and yet so detailed!
item_48018.Name: Amulet of the Pack

item_48019.Description: This is just some weird elven runes on a chain.
item_48019.Name: Eraphylle

item_48020.Description: This is just some weird elven runes on a chain.
item_48020.Name: Yyllastra

item_48021.Description: This is just some weird elven runes on a chain.
item_48021.Name: Eynophille

item_48022.Description: A tiny metal fist squeezing a man, who seems unperturbed. That's craftsmanship!
item_48022.Name: Amulet of Crushing Mitigation 1

item_48023.Description: A tiny metal fist squeezing a man, who seems unperturbed. That's craftsmanship!
item_48023.Name: Amulet of Crushing Mitigation 2

item_48024.Description: A tiny metal fist squeezing a man, who seems unperturbed. That's craftsmanship!
item_48024.Name: Amulet of Crushing Mitigation 3

item_48025.Description: A tiny metal fist squeezing a man, who seems unperturbed. That's craftsmanship!
item_48025.Name: Amulet of Crushing Mitigation 4

item_48026.Description: A tiny metal fist squeezing a man, who seems unperturbed. That's craftsmanship!
item_48026.Name: Amulet of Crushing Mitigation 5

item_48027.Description: A figurine of a tiny man with a sword in his skull, who seems to be unperturbed.
item_48027.Name: Amulet of Slashing Mitigation 1

item_48028.Description: A figurine of a tiny man with a sword in his skull, who seems to be unperturbed.
item_48028.Name: Amulet of Slashing Mitigation 2

item_48029.Description: A figurine of a tiny man with a sword in his skull, who seems to be unperturbed.
item_48029.Name: Amulet of Slashing Mitigation 3

item_48030.Description: A figurine of a tiny man with a sword in his skull, who seems to be unperturbed.
item_48030.Name: Amulet of Slashing Mitigation 4

item_48031.Description: A figurine of a tiny man with a sword in his skull, who seems to be unperturbed.
item_48031.Name: Amulet of Slashing Mitigation 5

item_48032.Description: A figurine of a man with an arrow in his back, who seems to be grinning.
item_48032.Name: Amulet of Piercing Mitigation 1

item_48033.Description: A figurine of a man with an arrow in his back, who seems to be grinning.
item_48033.Name: Amulet of Piercing Mitigation 2

item_48034.Description: A figurine of a man with an arrow in his back, who seems to be grinning.
item_48034.Name: Amulet of Piercing Mitigation 3

item_48035.Description: A figurine of a man with an arrow in his back, who seems to be grinning.
item_48035.Name: Amulet of Piercing Mitigation 4

item_48036.Description: A figurine of a man with an arrow in his back, who seems to be grinning.
item_48036.Name: Amulet of Piercing Mitigation 5

item_48038.Description: An elegant opal on a thin gold chain. Tasteful.
item_48038.Name: Rita's Charm

item_48039.Description: Hand-made from a leftover snail shell, and infused with simple magic by Sie's fairy friends.
item_48039.Name: Sie Antry's Talisman

item_48040.Description: A figurine of a smiling man with ice-entombed feet.
item_48040.Name: Amulet of Cold Mitigation 1

item_48041.Description: A medallion with an abstract design. Perhaps it is mantis claws raised in victory. Or in pain.
item_48041.Name: Elzehatl's Insignia

item_48042.Description: A figurine of a grinning skull. But, of course, all skulls grin. A necromancy gem is in the eye socket.
item_48042.Name: Necromancy Test Medallion

item_48043.Description: Made of blackened metal and etched with demonic runes.
item_48043.Name: Tidal's Circlet

item_48046.Description: Blackened as if from fire, this metal glyph emanates controlled rage. A soot-covered Necromancy Gem is still affixed on the back.
item_48046.Name: Symbol of Hate Made Manifest

item_48048.Description: A string covered in weird little beads and shells.
item_48048.Name: Fae Bead Necklace

item_48049.Description: Used by goblin necromancers. A necromancy gem has been embedded in a case made of bone shards.
item_48049.Name: Goblin Necromancy Focus

item_48050.Description: Used by the goblin necromancer Jumjab. It contains two different necromancy gems, in case one gets shattered in combat.
item_48050.Name: Jumjab's Compelling Augment

item_48051.Description: A weird elven rune on a chain. Unlike most elven rune amulets, this one was mass-produced in Verta for export to other lands. Not exactly a triumph of art, but its protective magic is undeniable.
item_48051.Name: Ulnaphylle

item_48052.Description: An expensive necklace with a well-cut magic tourmaline. This type of necklace is often used by people who fear they are in danger of having a psychotic break, although it can only hold off the inevitable for a little while.
item_48052.Name: Soothing Medallion

item_48053.Description: A figurine of a muscular human with a huge pack on his back.
item_48053.Name: Amulet of the Rugged Traveler

item_48054.Description: This is just some weird elven runes on a chain.
item_48054.Name: Alamyneth

item_48056.Description: A figurine of a tiny shield.
item_48056.Name: Amulet of Max Armor +50

item_48057.Description: A mirror on a chain with a subtle illusion. Enemies briefly see you as being far more beautiful than you are, then suddenly perceive you as being far uglier than reality. It's pretty unnerving.
item_48057.Name: Indicator of False Beauty

item_48058.Description: A tiny enchanted saw on a chain. But it's not just an amulet: upon command, the tiny saw can cut lumber at high speed! (This item acts as a handsaw.)
item_48058.Name: Cutting Blade Necklace

item_48059.Description: Foxes are beloved wizard familiars because they channel tremendous Power. This little metal image of a fox does too.
item_48059.Name: Fox Glyph

item_48060.Description: A fad item by the master of trend magic, Rea Shuloth. Rea's spell compelled everyone to love these necklaces, but even magic can't control fashion for long, and now these are seen as incredibly gauche.
item_48060.Name: Hexagonal Trendsetter

item_48061.Description: This bit of magical rhino horn can be worn as a makeshift necklace.
item_48061.Name: Rhino Necklace

item_48062.Description: A very old locket with a portrait of a human woman painted inside. The artistic quality is quite high. It is engraved, "Don't cry, but don't forget. Love always, Caroline."
item_48062.Name: Lord Serbule's Pendant

item_49001.Description: This ugly purple ring magically strengthens your ankles so that falling from great heights isn't quite as painful. It's a pretty weak enchantment, really.
item_49001.Name: Ring of Strong Ankles

item_49002.Description: This criminally ugly purple ring augments your movement so that your sprint speed is slightly faster.
item_49002.Name: Ring of Jaunty Traipsing

item_49003.Description: This cheap-looking purple ring makes poisons slightly less effective.
item_49003.Name: Ring of Vague Poison Resistance

item_49004.Description: This shoddily-made ring improves psychic attacks.
item_49004.Name: Ring of Telepathic Pestering

item_49005.Description: This tough-but-ugly ring makes Punch attacks deal more damage.
item_49005.Name: Ring of Trusty Punching

item_49006.Description: This vaguely-green metal ring improves an Unarmed ability: Cobra Strike.
item_49006.Name: Ring of Snakelike Behavior

item_49007.Description: This slightly off-white metal ring improves a Sword ability: Many Cuts.
item_49007.Name: Ring of Multiple Lacerations

item_49008.Description: This ring is slightly warm to the touch. It augments Fire Magic abilities that deal area-effect damage focused on the caster, such as Ring of Flames and Defensive Flames.
EffectDescs: Ring of Fire, Defensive Burst, and Defensive Chill deal +5 damage
item_49008.Name: Ring of Booming

item_49009.Description: This slightly off-white metal ring improves a Sword ability: Wind Strike.
item_49009.Name: Ring of Gusty Striking

item_49010.Description: This dull black ring improves a Psychology ability: Cause Terror.
item_49010.Name: Ring of Psychiatric Abuse

item_49011.Description: This mottled ring improves a Werewolf ability: Claw
item_49011.Name: Ring of Furry Clawing

item_49021.Description: This chunky blue ring augments any kind of kick, such as the Unarmed ability Kick or kicks done when in the form of a deer or other ungulate.
item_49021.Name: Ring of Kicking Ass

item_49022.Description: This ring glows a pale blue.
item_49022.Name: Ring of Armor Regeneration +5

item_49023.Description: This thick wooden ring feels surprisingly light.
item_49023.Name: Ring of Staff Supremacy

item_49024.Description: This jade ring thumps in time to the wearer's pulse, the better to tune into their mind.
item_49024.Name: Ring of Critical Hits

item_49025.Description: This ring has little barbs all along the outside. Takes some practice to wear it safely.
item_49025.Name: Ring of Natural Hurting

item_49026.Description: A disgusting ring coated in a perpetual layer of slime. But the slime isn't acid. It's just slime.
item_49026.Name: Ring of Acid Resistance

item_49028.Description: A gaudy golden ring with a purple enchantment aura.
item_49028.Name: Grand Ring

item_49029.Description: An arrowhead is embedded in this wooden ring, making it rather uncomfortable to wear.
item_49029.Name: Ring of Arrows

item_49030.Description: This mottled ring improves a Werewolf ability: Claw
item_49030.Name: Ring of Ferocious Clawing

item_49031.Description: Tyler gave this ring to his soulmate as a token of his affection.
item_49031.Name: Tyler's Ring

item_49032.Description: This ugly blue ring enhances most Psychology healing effects by 50.
item_49032.Name: Ring of Practical Psychology

item_49033.Description: This ring makes you unnoticeable by monsters, unless they see you in combat.
item_49033.Name: Admin Ring of Non-Detection

item_49035.Description: This gaudy gold heart ring looks more like a lovelorn elf's token of affection than some powerful magical device.
item_49035.Name: Ring of Health

item_49036.Description: Carved of bamboo and painted with magic pigments.
item_49036.Name: Stafflord's Ring

item_49037.Description: Made of pink wood, supposedly common in the orcish homeland of Gu.
item_49037.Name: Ring of Directness

item_49038.Description: This ring is blackened and pitted from (presumed) acid splashes.
item_49038.Name: Ring of Acid Blasting

item_49039.Description: This mottled ring improves a Werewolf ability: Smell Fear
item_49039.Name: Ring of Wolfen Terror

item_49040.Description: This wooden ring is carved with elven sword-runes.
item_49040.Name: Ring of Swording

item_49042.Description: Jade with scrimshaw glyphs that say "Wizards Rule" in elvish. Fortunately the inscription is on the inside of the ring where nobody can see it.
item_49042.Name: Arcane Ring

item_49043.Description: This gold ring is not particularly unique, but it was clearly made by dwarves.
item_49043.Name: Dwarven Ring

item_49044.Description: Made of dried root, this myconian-designed ring is not attractive, but it is comfortable.
item_49044.Name: Mindroot

item_49045.Description: This small metal band seems to get tighter and tighter the longer you wear it.
item_49045.Name: Ring of Increasing Anxiety

item_49046.Description: This ring seems ready to fly off your finger at any moment, but mercifully stays put.
item_49046.Name: Ring of Projectile Expression

item_49047.Description: So heavy! Wait, that's probably an illusion... nope, it really is super heavy. Makes it hard to hold stuff.
item_49047.Name: Heavy Ring

item_49048.Description: An ugly green ring that leaves a vaguely smelly odor behind.
item_49048.Name: Blight Ring

item_49049.Description: This grungy ring has a little scoop on the end to help you dig skulls out of corpses. (Acts as a skull extractor.)
item_49049.Name: Ring of Mind Insight

item_49050.Description: This piece of costume jewelry is so ugly that monsters tend to hate you just for wearing it.
item_49050.Name: Gaudy Ring of Sleaziness

item_49051.Description: A tiny ring made of an otherworldly metal.
item_49051.Name: Fae Ring of Healing

item_50001.Description: Designed to be worn at the base of a Rakshasa's tail, this improves the wearer's Righteousness, allowing them to forgo the negative effects of killing sentient creatures for longer.
item_50001.Name: Tail Ring of Righteousness

item_50002.Description: Designed to be worn at the base of a Rakshasa's tail, this allows the wearer to remember two additional map spots at a time. It is inscribed, "to Sinda, the explorer supreme."
item_50002.Name: Sinda's Tail Ring of Cartography

item_50003.Description: Designed to be worn in humans' pierced ears, these earrings boost the wearer's maximum capacity for enjoyment of others' company, allowing them to be alone longer without becoming miserable.
item_50003.Name: Earrings of Community

item_50004.Description: Designed to be worn in an elf's pierced navel, this small gemmed ring repels dust and dirt.
item_50004.Name: Navel Ring of Cleanliness

item_50005.Description: Designed to be worn in an elf's pierced navel, this small gemmed ring enhances the elf's biorhythms slightly.
item_50005.Name: Navel Ring of Health

item_50006.Description: Designed to be worn in an elf's pierced navel, this small gemmed ring enhances the elf's natural accuracy with a bow.
item_50006.Name: Navel Ring of Precision

item_50007.Description: Designed to be worn at the base of a Rakshasa's tail, this slows the rate at which hydration is lost, allowing the Rakshasa to function without water for twice as long.
item_50007.Name: Tail Ring of Hydration

item_50008.Description: Designed to be worn in a cow's nose, this brass ring further enhances natural bovine strength.
item_50008.Name: Nose Ring of Inexhaustability

item_50009.Description: Simple but high-quality, these earrings were worn by a human who lived in the desert years ago. They can be worn in humans' pierced ears.
item_50009.Name: Bonnie's Earrings

item_50011.Description: Designed to be worn at the base of a Rakshasa's tail, this imperceptibly alters a Rakshasa's mind.
item_50011.Name: Tail Ring of Defiance

item_50012.Description: Designed to be worn in a cow's nose, this brass ring makes attractive cattle even more attractive.
EffectDescs: But I Love You deals +30 damage
item_50012.Name: Nose Ring of The Seductive Cow

item_50013.Description: Designed to be worn at the base of a deer's tail, this brass ring is very cute.
item_50013.Name: White-Tail Ring

item_50014.Description: Designed to be worn at the base of a deer's tail, this brass ring enhances ferocity.
item_50014.Name: Black-Tail Ring

item_50015.Description: Designed to be worn in a cow's nose, this brass ring aggravates bovine sensibilities, causing violence.
item_50015.Name: Nose Ring of Destructive Tendencies

item_51001.Description: Good for flinging small amounts of chemicals all around you. Held in the main hand.
item_51001.Name: Basic Combat Beaker

item_51002.Description: An extraordinary staff with an alchemical beaker on the end. You can use this for staff fighting or battle chemistry. It's not suitable for fire magic, though.
item_51002.Name: Hogan's Flingin' Stick

item_51003.Description: An unusual staff with an alchemical beaker on the end. Not suitable for casting Fire Magic.
item_51003.Name: Beaker-Stick

item_51004.Description: A beaker for flinging chemicals in combat. Held in the main hand.
item_51004.Name: Acid Beaker

item_51005.Description: A beaker for flinging chemicals in combat. Held in the main hand.
item_51005.Name: Splash Beaker

item_51006.Description: This beaker has been carefully constructed to keep healing chemicals at a lower temperature, slightly improving their effects. Held in the main hand.
item_51006.Name: Recuperative Beaker

item_51007.Description: This beaker is one of Xegatis' early failed attempts at restoring flesh to Nightmare Creatures. A crude Necromancy Gem is embedded in the bottom.
item_51007.Name: Beaker of Xegatis

item_51008.Description: The story goes that a crazed elf spent a hundred years splashing himself with different acid beakers to find the one that hurt the most. This is that beaker.
item_51008.Name: Maiming Beaker

item_51009.Description: This old beaker is perfectly shaped for gulping down quick-brewed healing concoctions.
item_51009.Name: Chugging Beaker

item_51010.Description: Good for flinging small amounts of chemicals all around you. Held in the main hand.
item_51010.Name: Basic Combat Beaker

item_51011.Description: Good for flinging small amounts of chemicals all around you. Held in the off hand.
item_51011.Name: Basic Combat Flask

item_51012.Description: A flask for flinging chemicals in combat. Held in the off hand.
item_51012.Name: Acid Flask

item_51013.Description: A flask for flinging chemicals in combat. Held in the off hand.
item_51013.Name: Splash Flask

item_51014.Description: This flask has been carefully constructed to keep healing chemicals at a lower temperature, slightly improving their effects. Held in the off hand.
item_51014.Name: Recuperative Flask

item_51015.Description: The great alchemists of yore supposedly used flasks like this when they fought in wars. Or perhaps that's just a tale invented to sell flasks.
item_51015.Name: War Flask

item_51016.Description: This old flask is perfectly shaped for gulping down quick-brewed healing concoctions.
item_51016.Name: Chugging Flask

item_51017.Description: Good for flinging small amounts of chemicals all around you. Held in the off hand.
item_51017.Name: Basic Combat Flask

item_51018.Description: While dwarves are mostly known for brewing alcohol, those same techniques can also be used to brew potent offensive chemicals.
item_51018.Name: Dwarven Brewer Flask

item_51019.Description: The creator of this beaker designed it around what he thought dwarves would use in combat. He was utterly wrong in every way, but the beaker is still pretty powerful.
item_51019.Name: Dwarf-Inspired Beaker

item_51020.Description: A beaker for exploding stuff. Held in the main hand.
item_51020.Name: Bombing Beaker

item_51021.Description: This cunningly made flask is slightly askew, causing chemicals to spray everywhere. Only experts can hope to use it in combat.
item_51021.Name: Lopsided Flask

item_51022.Description: The sneaky crone Anhinda made this flask after decades of trial and error.
item_51022.Name: Anhinda's Flask

item_52001.Description: Once a fine weapon, this bow has been mistreated for a very long time. It still shoots arrows, though.
item_52001.Name: Old Worn Bow

item_52002.Description: A mass-produced longbow made for infantrymen to use in a bind. Nothing special.
item_52002.Name: Stock Bow

item_52003.Description: An Elven bow made by someone with a lot of time on their hands. (An Elf, in other words.)
item_52003.Name: Hunting Bow

item_52004.Description: An Elven bow that's been enhanced with Goblin magic.
item_52004.Name: Goblinized Bow

item_52005.Description: Although technically Orcish, these bows are made by Dwarven conscripts.
item_52005.Name: Un-Tal Bow

item_52006.Description: Hand-made by a bored bowyer of middling skill. But it makes a twangy sound and the arrows go forward, so what do you want?
item_52006.Name: Basic Bow

item_52007.Description: Apparently once used by Lawara, an elf you met in on an island. It's high-quality, and has a custom hand plate that provides a bit of shielding.
item_52007.Name: Lawara's Bow

item_52008.Description: Tremor the Myconian took this bow from a pesky elf. Myconians can't use bows, but Tremor liked plucking the string to make a 'twang' sound. It really irritated other myconians, and Tremor liked that.
item_52008.Name: Tremor's Bow

item_52009.Description: Practically oozing with enchantment, this masterpiece is rarely seen outside of Elven lands.
item_52009.Name: Elven Master Bow

item_52010.Description: Dwarves aren't really great at making bows with decent range. But this bow is very sturdy!
item_52010.Name: Dwarven Bashbow

item_52011.Description: A light bow designed for precision over power.
item_52011.Name: Eltibule Bow

item_52012.Description: Crafted by goblin slaves under the watchful eye of Gyrumpa, the legendary bowyer. He hated fun, and made sure his bows were especially taxing to use.
item_52012.Name: Goblinic Piercer

item_52013.Description: Tremor the Myconian took this bow from a pesky elf. Myconians can't use bows, but Tremor liked plucking the string to make a 'twang' sound. It really irritated other myconians, and Tremor liked that.
item_52013.Name: Tremor's Enhanced Bow

item_52014.Description: The Dwarven Stalwarts had to overcome their prejudice against ranged weapons. They developed this bludgeoning bow which acknowledges the value of archery while still insisting that hammers are better.
item_52014.Name: Stalwart Bow

item_52015.Description: A rakshasa craftsman named Malgath once used this to demonstrate his skill at crafting.
item_52015.Name: Malgath's Demo Bow

item_52016.Description: A longbow optimized for long-distance targets.
item_52016.Name: Bow of Range

item_52017.Description: A longbow optimized for quick shots.
item_52017.Name: Fastbow

item_52018.Description: A fairly-new item made in the Rakshasa manner, but probably not by a Rakshasa. Still not terrible.
item_52018.Name: Replica Rakshasa Bow

item_52019.Description: A competent and accurate weapon made by the elves of Sedgewick Forest.
item_52019.Name: Thentree Bow

item_52020.Description: A scarred and twisted bow, barely able to be strung. A hum of darkness can be felt from within. A tiny necromancy gem is embedded in the top.
item_52020.Name: Blackened Bow

item_52021.Description: These lightweight bows aren't actually used by the Peltasts of the Crone Hegemony, but by their support archers.
item_52021.Name: Peltast Bow

item_52022.Description: An Elven bow that's been enhanced with shoddy Goblin magic.
item_52022.Name: Cheap Goblinized Bow

item_53001.Description: Made by an amateur, this punching weapon barely fits onto your hand. But sometimes an ugly, stupid-looking weapon can inspire more fear than a good weapon. Not really. But keep thinking that while you wear these.
item_53001.Name: Shoddy Brass Knuckles

item_53002.Description: They've turned all green and gross. But they'll still work to make your punches more painful.
item_53002.Name: Corroded Brass Knuckles

item_53003.Description: These fit over your knuckles to make your punches hurt more. Now with real faux-brass coating!
item_53003.Name: Basic Brass Knuckles

item_53004.Description: Designed to fit over leather gloves, these brass knuckles have nasty bumps to make your punches cause extra injury.
item_53004.Name: Protruding Knuckles

item_53005.Description: It's sturdy, but it's so simple that it'd be hard not to be sturdy. But it's not false advertising, anyway.
item_53005.Name: Sturdy Cestus

item_53006.Description: This simple fist weapon was fitted for a goblin's hand, but you can make it work. (Cestuses count as an empty hand for purposes of Unarmed attacks.)
item_53006.Name: Goblin Cestus

item_53007.Description: This simple fist weapon will make your punches hurt more.
item_53007.Name: Quality Cestus

item_53008.Description: This simple fist weapon will make your punches hurt more.
item_53008.Name: Quality Cestus

item_53009.Description: Preferred by orcish martial artists, this black-iron fist weapon is intimidatingly heavy in the hand.
item_53009.Name: Orcish Katar

item_53011.Description: This grim fist weapon was clearly inspired by the Human legend of the Green Man, a druid who supposedly wanders the forests and punches wayword teens to death if they're out past curfew.
item_53011.Name: Fist of the Green Man

item_53012.Description: It was found in the gut of a giant spider. That's really the only spider-related thing going on here.
item_53012.Name: Spider Cestus

item_53013.Description: The preferred punching thingy of elven bullies.
item_53013.Name: Elven Cestus

item_53014.Description: It's a bit cramped for larger races, but this Dwarven unarmed weapon feels impressively heavy.
item_53014.Name: Dwarven Pugilfist

item_53015.Description: A piece of arm machinery from a large ancient golem.
item_53015.Name: Golem Fist

item_53016.Description: This punching weapon has a little mechanical serpent head on it which can be used to inject poison deep into a target.
item_53016.Name: Serpent Sting

item_53017.Description: This is just a piece of metal, but it's been covered in strange substances that help protect the hand of the puncher.
item_53017.Name: Yeti Knuckleduster

item_53018.Description: Someone has carved a fist weapon out of glasstone, a rock known for its supernatural lightness. The glasstone market is in shambles now that glasstone jewelry has fallen out of fashion among humans, so new uses are becoming affordable.
item_53018.Name: Glassstone Fist

item_53501.Description: Some bones strapped to a handle make this off-hand martial weapon look as stupid as it feels.
item_53501.Name: Shoddy Fighting Claw

item_53502.Description: Sharpened bone "blades" protrude from this off-hand martial weapon. It's silly looking, but dangerous!
item_53502.Name: Primitive Fighting Claw

item_53503.Description: This martial artist's glove is adorned with small sharpened metal protrusions. It smells like soup.
item_53503.Name: Goblin Claw

item_53504.Description: Fashionable, but a little uncomfortable to wear unless you're a Rakshasa.
item_53504.Name: Sturdy Claw

item_53505.Description: A skilled metalsmith put this left-handed fighting claw together. It's a little uncomfortable to wear, though.
item_53505.Name: Quality Claw

item_53506.Description: A skilled metalsmith put this left-handed fighting claw together. It's a little uncomfortable to wear, though.
item_53506.Name: Quality Claw

item_53507.Description: The Rakshasa martial artist handed this weapon down to a promising pupil.
item_53507.Name: Furlak's Claw

item_53508.Description: Long, deadly blades jut out from this glove-like weapon. It only fits the left hand.
item_53508.Name: Basic War Claw

item_53509.Description: When the Council demanded that the Rakshasa provide renumeration for every human that was injured at the Battle of Rahu, outraged Rakshasa tore up the treaty and killed the messengers, leading to the Sand War. The Rakshasa won the war with claws like this, fashioned after weapons from their home world.
item_53509.Name: Sand War Claw

item_53510.Description: Made of Cold Iron, this weapon is used in fae civil wars. Fairies who wield it are in constant pain from the metal... but not as much pain as their victims.
item_53510.Name: Fae Claw

item_53511.Description: The deadly elf Leopold wore this claw. Until he died.
item_53511.Name: Leopold's Claw

item_53512.Description: Few of the legendary Dwarven Stalwarts used unarmed weapons, but the ones that did wore claws like this.
item_53512.Name: Stalwart Claw

item_53513.Description: The Rakshasa outcasts in the Ilmari Desert enchant these claws with life-saving protection from the desert elements.
item_53513.Name: Resistant Claw

item_53514.Description: A claw enchanted specifically for making horrible scars.
item_53514.Name: Torturer's Claw

item_53515.Description: A claw tailored specifically for the Claw Barrage maneuver.
item_53515.Name: Claw-Barrager

item_53516.Description: A claw with ugly tassels dangling from it. Being hit by this stupid-looking weapon is especially infuriating.
item_53516.Name: Ridiculer's Claw

EffectDescs: Equipping this item grants you basic proficiency in stringed instrument performance.
item_54001.Name: Classic Lute

EffectDescs: Equipping this item grants you basic proficiency in percussion instrument performance.
item_54002.Name: Hand Drum

EffectDescs: Equipping this item grants you basic proficiency in wind instrument performance.
item_54003.Name: Gemshorn

item_54004.Description: A brass horn of dwarven design.
EffectDescs: Equipping this item grants you basic proficiency in its use, assuming you already have mastery of the ocarina.
item_54004.Name: Blatterhorn

EffectDescs: Equipping this item grants you basic proficiency in its use, assuming you already have mastery of the drum.
item_54005.Name: Mini-Dulcimer

item_54006.Description: A tiny harp. Sounds pretty good.
EffectDescs: Equipping this item grants you basic proficiency in its use, assuming you already have mastery of the lute.
item_54006.Name: Harp

item_55001.Description: It's glass with some kind of chemicals in it.
item_55001.Name: Warmth Orb

item_55002.Description: It's a pool of liquid heat energy trapped in special glass.
item_55002.Name: Heat Orb

item_55003.Description: It's heat energy trapped in glass. It's hot to the touch.
item_55003.Name: Fire Orb

item_55004.Description: It's heat energy trapped in glass. It's hot to the touch.
item_55004.Name: Burning Orb

item_55006.Name: Incinerating Orb

item_55101.Description: Somehow this glass orb has a bit of depression trapped within it. Dark emotions are power for Necromancy, and this orb can be used as a Necromancy Gem.
item_55101.Name: Suicide Orb

item_55102.Description: Somehow this glass orb has pure revulsion trapped within it. Dark emotions are power for Necromancy, and this orb can be used as a Necromancy Gem.
item_55102.Name: Revulsion Orb

item_55103.Description: Somehow this glass orb has pure anguish trapped inside it. Dark emotions are power for Necromancy, and this orb can be used as a Necromancy Gem.
item_55103.Name: Anguish Orb

item_55104.Description: Somehow this glass orb has pure despair trapped within it. Dark emotions are power for Necromancy, and this orb can be used as a Necromancy Gem.
item_55104.Name: Despair Orb

item_55105.Description: Somehow this glass orb has raw emotional hate trapped inside it. Dark emotions are power for Necromancy, and this orb can be used as a Necromancy Gem.
item_55105.Name: Hate Orb

item_55106.Description: There are six nature spirits responsible for creating the undead. Gulagra, the spirit of chaos, is not one of them. But don't try to tell him that.
item_55106.Name: Gulagra Orb

item_55107.Description: This glass orb contains a tiny bit of the essence of fury. It can be used as a Necromancy Gem, but it should not be wielded by those lacking self-control.
item_55107.Name: Fury Orb

item_55503.Description: It's a lumpy stick, but it's had the splinters removed.
item_55503.Name: Primitive Club

item_55504.Description: A lumpy stick with protruding thorns around the outside.
item_55504.Name: Vicious Club

item_55505.Description: The Flower Child liked to lovingly poke people with this dainty stick.
item_55505.Name: The Flower Child's Prodder

item_55506.Description: A very nasty very heavy stick.
item_55506.Name: Cruel Club

item_55507.Description: Agrashab used this club for a while before he found a better one.
item_55507.Name: Agrashab's Club

item_55508.Description: Gulagra, the spirit of discord, usually takes the form of a mountain-sized worm, and would have no use for this club. But somebody named it after him anyway.
item_55508.Name: Gulagra's Club

item_55509.Description: This legendary anti-troll device is imbued with magic flame that can never be quenched. There are rumors that sometimes the club's wielder gets a tiny bit incinerated when the fire gets out of control... but what are you, a baby?
EffectDescs: All Hammer attacks have a 25% chance to ignite the target, causing 50 damage over 20 seconds
item_55509.Name: Flame Basher

item_55510.Description: This huge club has been used to kill so many drakeworms that some of their strange magic has rubbed off on it.
item_55510.Name: Deworming Club

item_55511.Description: Archtroll merchants in the fae realm sell these clubs as souvenirs to rich magical tourists. Very few tourists realize the exceptional quality they're purchasing, and most are thrown away as junk a few years later.
item_55511.Name: Archcudgel

item_55602.Description: Thick and awkward, but basically indestructible.
item_55602.Name: Dwarven Hammer

item_55603.Description: This hammer has little rivulets carved into it to guide any blood away from the wielder's hand. Craftsmanship!
item_55603.Name: Battle Hammer

item_55604.Description: Perfect for hitting enemies and then shooting them with lightning. Much less practical for construction work.
item_55604.Name: Blasting Hammer

item_55605.Description: Covered in weird runes. Probably just graffiti.
item_55605.Name: Hammer of the Five Truths

item_55606.Description: Standard issue for the ancient Dwarven Stalwarts. They don't make them like this anymore.
item_55606.Name: Stalwart Hammer

item_55607.Description: This ungainly hammer has an inscription: 'Not even their bones must survive. - Ku Turla'
item_55607.Name: Mallet of Obliteration

item_55608.Description: A huge weighted hammer that can only be wielded by mighty warriors. It is said that a minotaur may not criticize their elders until they can wield this hammer -- a task that requires years of training even for that gigantic race.
item_55608.Name: Minotaur Hammer

item_55609.Description: Asterion the minotaur customized this ridiculously heavy hammer to be even heavier. A phrase is inscribed on the shaft in common tongue: "If you cannot lift my hammer, I shall lift it for you."
item_55609.Name: Asterion's Hammer
